title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, vanilla and milk together.
Slice butter on the bottom of casserole dish.
Pour batter over butter.
Pour quart of fruit over batter (any kind of fruit).
Bake until batter comes to the top and browns.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Grease 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Arrange 5 slices of bread, layer of cheese and sausage.
Arrange rest of bread and sausage.
Blend eggs and other ingredients.
Pour over casserole. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: quick meat casserole
directions: You could also use Heinz home-style savory brown gravy or Pepperidge Farm brand gravy.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, butter and eggs and cream.
Sift the flour, cream of tartar, salt and baking soda together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Put into refrigerator to chill so it can be handled.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll balls in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press each cookie with a damp cloth.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: wassail (holiday beverage)
directions: Simmer first 5 ingredients for about an hour.
Strain.
Add sugar and cider that has been heated.
Serve with an orange slice and a whole clove in each punch cup or float them in a punch bowl.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Combine raisins, coffee, crisco, salt, sugar, cinnamon and cloves in saucepan let simmer 5 minutes.
Let mixture cool.
When cool add flour, baking soda and baking powder and mix well.
Add to this mixture the apple sauce, walnuts, mixed fruits and maraschino cherries.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350 or until golden brown.
When cake is cooled, pour wine or brandy over the top.

title: orange fluff salad
directions: Mix pineapple with jello.
Add cottage cheese, Cool Whip and nuts.
Mix and chill.

title: lace cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, well beaten. Add pecans and raisins. Drop very small amount on warm metal sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter in pan; add sugar, milk and salt.
Cook until it begins to boil.
Time it for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. After 10 minutes, test a small amount in cold water.
If it rolls up in a ball, it is done.
If not done, cook 1 more minute.
Take off fire; add peanut butter, vanilla and marshmallow cream.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into a butter-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool before cutting.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 500° for 25 minutes.

title: brisket of beef
directions: Place brisket on sheet of heavy-duty foil, fat side down. Sprinkle soup mix on top of brisket.
Close foil tightly, no leaks.
Set oven at 200°.
Roast for 7 hours.

title: baked tomatoes and corn
directions: Simmer all ingredients except bread crumbs and cheese 15 minutes.
Place 1/3 mixture in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Repeat with mixture and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crown jewel patties
directions: Beat egg.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
(If mix is too wet, add more bread crumbs.)
Shape into patties.
Coat with cornflakes.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 55 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix dry pudding and other ingredients together; chill.

title: brownies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Combine with oats and brown sugar.
Stir in melted butter or margarine.
Pat mixture in bottom of 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Place sausage in a bowl with cheese and Bisquick.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until well done.
Pull apart or off of bone if not boneless.
Cover biscuits with flour and roll thin and cut into 3 or 4 slices each.
Drop into hot chicken broth and add milk and cook until done.
Put chicken back into gravy mixture and add salt and pepper.
You must stir often to keep from sticking (30 to 40 minutes).

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Put into buttered dish. Sprinkle top with the cheese and crackers. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: dianne's chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt, margarine and milk in a large pot.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 8 to 9 minutes, still stirring.

title: cranberry fluff salad
directions: Combine chopped cranberries, marshmallows and sugar.
Cover and chill overnight.
Add pineapple and nuts, mixing well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar together.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into a greased 10 x 10-inch cake pan or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cherry pineapple cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add sifted dry ingredients: zucchini, carrots, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a 3 1/2-quart crock-pot in order listed.
Cook 4 1/2 to 5 hours on high or 8 to 10 hours on low.

title: fat-free potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes. Stir until smooth.
Add small amount of salt and pepper to potatoes.
Stir all ingredients together until well blended.

title: microwave peanut brittle #1
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook 8 minutes on High (stirring well after 4 minutes).
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 minutes longer on High.
Remove from oven and quickly stir in soda until light and foamy.
Immediately pour onto a lightly greased baking sheet; spread out thinly.
When cool, break into small pieces.
Store in an airtight container.
Yields 1 pound.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Press 1/2 of ground chuck into casserole dish, then add layer of onion, a layer of potato slices and a layer of cheese.
Repeat in same order.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soup and water and pour over the mixture.
Cover and bake for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: marge's cabbage rolls
directions: Remove center from head of cabbage.
Place cabbage head in large pan and cover with water.
Add vinegar.
Cook until leaves become soft and can be removed.
Line roaster pan bottom with some of the cooked cabbage leaves.
Mix hamburger, sausage, rice and seasonings together.
Place mixture on individual leaves and roll. Wrap with bacon slice and secure with a toothpick.
Place in roaster.
Dissolve 4 beef bouillon cubes in juice from cooked cabbage and pour over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, uncovered.

title: chicken treat
directions: Beat chicken breast with mallet until 1/4-inch thick.
Place 1 slice ham, diced tomato and 1 slice Mozzarella cheese on chicken breast.
Roll up and place wood skewer or toothpick to hold roll. Dip in milk; roll in mixture of bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and spices.
Place on foiled baking (cookie or shallow) pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with curried rice and steamed fresh green beans.

title: savory pinto beans
directions: Place all ingredients except the cheese in a large pot.
Cover with water.
Bring to a slow boil.
Cook until beans are soft (1 1/2 to 2 hours), replenishing water as needed.

title: apple cream coffee cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Mix sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Spread half the batter on well-greased pan, all apples and half the cinnamon/nut mixture.
Add rest of mixture and put remaining cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done when tested.

title: crawfish or shrimp jambalaya
directions: Saute veggies in margarine.
Add crawfish and cook until pink. Mix remaining ingredients, add to mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sheath cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Combine oleo, oil, cocoa and flour mixture; stir.
Add milk, soda, eggs, cinnamon and vanilla. Pour into greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: tangy salad dressing
directions: Mix thoroughly in electric blender.
(Taste and add whatever you think necessary.)
Makes almost a quart of dressing.
Keeps very good in refrigerator.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Melt butter; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup milk gradually and cook over low heat for 5 minutes, until thick. Add 1 pound salmon, 1 egg and 1 cup crackers.
Cool and shape into patties.
Roll in 1 egg, then in cracker crumbs.
Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Moist and no fishy taste.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in medium bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in lemon peel and juice.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the Cool Whip.
Spread evenly in bottom of crust. Press strawberry halves into cream cheese layer.
Save some strawberries for a garnish if you like.

title: stuffed hog maw
directions: Soak pig's stomach in salt water for one hour.
Rinse.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Stuff the mixture into the pig's stomach tightly.
Close stomach with skewers.
Bake in roast pan with 3 cups water at 375° for about 4 hours.
Slice thickly and serve.

title: berry easy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Brush on meat or chicken at end of grilling time.
Makes 3 1/2 cups sauce (enough for 18 to 21 pounds of ribs).
Use it for ribs, pork chops, ham or chicken.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix the 6 ingredients together.

title: crunchy cheesecake bars
directions: Mix flour and brown sugar together in medium sized bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
(Set aside 1/2 cup of this mixture for topping.)
Press remaining mixture into bottom of ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients for 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.
Top of bread will crack.
When bread is done, remove from pans.
Frost while warm with:

title: tuna and rice
directions: Mix tuna, soup, rice and water until creamy.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until it is slightly thickened.
Place cheese slices on top and melt. Casserole thickens as it cools.
Reheats well.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine the 3 ingredients at room temperature.
Form into small balls that could be served on a toothpick.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.
Cooked balls may be frozen.

title: frozen salad
directions: In a large bowl combine OJ, water and sugar.
Slice bananas into OJ mixture to prevent darkening.
Add pineapple.
Chop apricot halves, slice peaches and cherries into bite size pieces.
Add to mixture.
Add strawberries and grapes.
Mix well.
Cover and freeze.
Remove from freezer about 45 - 60 minutes prior to serving.
When ready to serve pour 1 - 1.5 cans of 7-Up over frozen fruit mixture.
Serve partially frozen.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix apples, raisins and pecans in a bowl.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, sugar and egg.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in casserole dish or baking pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon over mixture.
Melt 1/4 stick margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can put ice cream or whipped cream on top when done.

title: honey-apple glazed hens with rice pilaf
directions: Remove and discard giblets from hens.
Rinse hens under cold running water and pat dry.
Remove skin and trim excess fat; split hens in half lengthwise.
Set aside.

title: cheese cake
directions: Place first three ingredients in medium saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add lemon jello and cream cheese.
Beat together well until smooth.
Fold in whipped Carnation cream.
Make graham cracker crust or use ready made.
Pour cream cheese mixture into crust.

title: custard bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
Soak in milk until soft.
Beat well with an egg beater.
Heat until nearly boiling.
Beat eggs well, add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Mix with bread and milk.
Add raisins.
Pour onto a 2-quart baking dish.
Set in a pan of warm water.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: company cheese dip
directions: Blend cream into cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and serve with raw vegetables or crackers or chips.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Cook bacon in Dutch oven until about done.
Add chopped onion. Cook until transparent.
Add tomato juice.
Cook to a slow boil. Add cayenne pepper and stir well.
Add okra.
Simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally from bottom.
Add brown sugar and simmer 5 minutes.
Skim off excess grease.
Freezes well.

title: easy spaghetti meat sauce for 25
directions: Brown ground beef in an 8-quart Dutch oven, stirring until it crumbles.
Drain well.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, dried onion flakes, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and pepper.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Spoon meat sauce over cooked spaghetti and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: toss and bake italian potatoes
directions: Toss potatoes with dressing and cheese.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: famous chocolate refrigerator rolls
directions: Use 2 cups heavy cream to 1 full box of chocolate wafers.

title: stir-n-drop cookies
directions: Using dinner fork, beat eggs, oil, sugar, lemon rind and vanilla until thoroughly mixed.
Add dry ingredients; mix well. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheets.
Stamp with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake until lightly brown on edges.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix one at a time in order given.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon well.
Coat pecans well with the egg white mixture, then the sugar mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in well sealed container when cool.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out the dough onto floured surface.
Use your favorite cookie cutter.
Bake at 325 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Enjoy!

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and eggs; add the vanilla and melted shortening.
Add the milk alternately with mixed dry ingredients. Roll the dough out on a floured board and cut the cookies.
Do not roll the cookies too thin.
Bake until almost browned at about 350°.

title: low calorie tomato dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl until well blended. Chill.

title: hershey's easy does it brownies
directions: Blend melted butter or margarine, sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and beat well with a spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Spread in 8-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brownie pulls away from edges of pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
I add 2/3 cup chopped pecans to this recipe.

title: impossible triple cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Mix together cheeses and spread evenly in bottom of pie plate.
Beat eggs, milk and Bisquick until smooth.
Pour into plate and top with the onions.
Bake about 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted into center of pie.

title: easy peanut butter mini cheesecakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line medium muffin pan with 12 muffin paper cups.
Place one vanilla wafer (flat side down) in each muffin cup.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy in medium bowl.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Fill muffin cups with mixture half full.
Place one Reese's peanut butter cup in each muffin cup.
Bake 15 minutes.
Allow to cool completely before serving.

title: meat balls and brown gravy
directions: In large bowl mix meat, eggs, onions, garlic, salt and cracker crumbs.
Roll out in small balls.
Brown in skillet.

title: banana cake
directions: In a bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add banana, buttermilk, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed until combined.
Beat on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8 x 1 1/2-inch or 9 x 1 1/2-inch round or 1 (9 x 13-inch) oblong pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on racks for 10 minutes.
Remove round cakes; cool on racks.
Serves 12.

title: little kid's "play dough"
directions: Mix al ingredients well. Let child play with it. Keep in plastic bag when not in use.
Add food coloring for various colors of dough.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into two loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
If using plain flour, add soda and salt.

title: cactus hills cracker jack
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine popcorn and peanuts in a metal bowl or on a cookie sheet. Place in the preheated oven.

title: kajan shrimp
directions: Fry butter, garlic, spices, sauce and tomato 7 to 8 minutes. Add shrimp until pink.
Serve over pasta.

title: hot pizza dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and Italian seasonings; spread into 8-inch pie pan. In a small bowl, combine Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle 1/2 on top of the cream cheese. Spread pizza sauce over the cheese mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Top with bell pepper and green onion. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Serve with French bread or vegetable dippers.

title: microwave taco casserole
directions: Place meat in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook in microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until beef is cooked.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain well.
Combine with remaining ingredients, except corn chips and cheese.
Spoon meat mixture over 2 cups of corn chips in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook in microwave on High for 5 minutes or until heated through.
Crush remaining corn chips.
Sprinkle casserole with corn chips and cheese.
Heat in microwave on Medium for 1 minute or until cheese is melted.

title: shrimp dip or spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter or margarine at room temperature. Add shrimp and a little garlic powder.
Add minced onion to taste. Serve with crackers for spreading or with chips for dipping. Serves 2 cups.

title: yogurt popsicles
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Fill plastic molds or ice cube trays and freeze.

title: curry chicken glaze
directions: Combine flour, salt and ginger in a paper bag.
Add chicken and shake to coat well.
Melt butter or margarine in a large, shallow pan.

Roll the chicken in the melted butter to coat well then arrange in a shallow casserole (don't pour on extra butter). Bake, uncovered, in hot oven at 375° for 20 minutes or until beginning to turn golden.

title: almost candy bars
directions: Mix cake mix and butter until crumbly and press into sheet cake pan.
Layer topping ingredients on top of cake mixture. Finish with condensed milk.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Slice mushrooms through cap and steam cook with onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Add flour and blend. Add stock.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Cook slightly and add cream and seasoning.
Heat through. Serve at once.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together one day prior to serving.
Store in refrigerator, stirring once or twice to be sure flavors are well blended.

title: hot rice
directions: Fry sausage and onion; drain.
Bring 6 cups of water to boil. Add rice and cook on high for 10 minutes.
Reduce to medium heat and stir in 1 package of soup mix.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and sausage and stir well.
Turn heat off; cover and let stand for 10 minutes.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Beat eggs and sugar together. Add to butter.
Add dates and stir; cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from heat and add rice cereal, nuts and vanilla.
Make into small balls about the size of a quarter and roll in flaked coconut.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except English muffins).
Cut muffins (each half) into 6 pieces.
Dab mixture onto each muffin piece and broil 8 to 10 minutes; or mix all ingredients and place mixture in oven dish.
Bake until bubbly in 350° oven and use with crackers as a hot dip.

title: tana's taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of ovenproof dish.
Layer salsa, then grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve hot with taco chips.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: In a large bowl, stir with fork, the flour, sugar and salt. Cut in shortening until crumbly.
In small bowl, beat together egg, water and vinegar.
Add to flour mixture until well moistened; divide dough into 5 portions and shape into a flat round patty, ready for rolling.
Wrap each in plastic or waxed paper; chill at least 30 minutes.
Add more flour for rolling and handling too much will not effect this dough.
It will keep in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days.

title: hanukkah food potato pancakes(latkes)
directions: Mix all ingredients together; form into balls and fry in hot grease, flattening as the latkes cook.
Brown on both sides. Serve with applesauce and sour cream.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Mix until well blended. Drop by level tablespoon 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges of cookies are lightly browned, but cookies are still soft.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown meat with onion, salt and pepper. Add juice and soups.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Add frozen vegetables and let simmer on low until vegetables are tender.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Cover and refrigerate for 5 hours.
Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: fast and festive fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill and serve. Serves 30.

title: shrimp and rice salad
directions: Cook rice and peas.
While rice is hot, add oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and tarragon.
Toss slightly; cool, then add peppers, parsley, green onions, peas, shrimp and olives.
Mix and cover bowl.
Refrigerate when ready to serve; top with watercress sprigs.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix butter, onion and rice; stir constantly until lightly brown.
Pour consomme with 1/2 cup of water over rice.
Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes.
Put mushrooms in about 10 minutes before done.

title: sesame butterfly chops
directions: Heat sesame oil in nonstick pan over medium heat.
Add chops and brown, sprinkling with sesame seed and ginger.
When both sides are browned, add soy sauce and white wine to skillet.
Add mushrooms and onions; stir gently to saute 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove chops to serving platter.
Add butter to pan; stir constantly to deglaze pan.
Pour mushroom-onion sauce over chops to serve. Serves 4.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: In a mixing bowl combine sugar, crisco, butter and one egg at a time until blended well.	Add salt, flour mixture alternated with milk.	Add flavoring.	Pour in tube pan, bake at 325° for one hour and ten minutes.

title: double-chocolate walnut brownies
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes; makes about 2 dozen.
Melt butter and chocolate in medium saucepan over moderate heat (may also be melted in microwave oven).
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Stir in one cup of walnuts.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix rest of walnuts and chocolate pieces and sprinkle over top of brownie mixture, pressing down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until top springs back when pressed with fingertip. Cook completely in pan.
Cut into bars.

title: pumpkin and mincemeat muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Beat together the eggs, pumpkin, oil and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Add mincemeat and a few chopped walnuts.
Bake in 350° oven until done.
These make nice big muffins.

title: golden potato soup
directions: Combine butter, flour, milk and hot water to make thick white sauce.
Add cheese, peanut butter, sugar, salt and pepper.
Beat in potatoes.
Add boiling water, stirring until smooth.
Add more boiling water or hot milk if needed to make desired consistency.

title: shrimpies(sean's favorite)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on halved English muffins.
Freeze 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into quarters.
Refreeze in freezer bag for future use.

title: triple layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt the margarine in the oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over the margarine.
Top evenly with coconut, then the sweetened condensed milk.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
In a small saucepan over low heat, melt the chocolate chips with the peanut butter.
Spread evenly over the coconut layer.
Cool 30 minutes.
Chill thoroughly and cut into bars.

title: margaret's corn salad
directions: *The whole green onion, including the top green part.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream pie
directions: In pan, melt evaporated milk, salt and chocolate chips.
Add marshmallows and let them melt.
Soften ice cream and spread in pie crust.
Pour sauce over ice cream and freeze 2 hours.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Place potatoes in 2-quart casserole dish and cover with other ingredients mixed together.
Bake 1 1/4 hours, covered, then uncover and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake 15 minutes more or until cheese melts.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Mix this marinade together in a bowl.
Wash 4 to 8 pieces of chicken breasts and place in baking pan.
Pour marinade over chicken.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: pizza balls
directions: Mix sausage, baking mix and cheeses with hands until all mix is absorbed.
Form into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 23 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Peel, slice and boil potatoes. Beat sour cream and cream cheese together. Add hot potatoes and beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole. Dot with butter and sprinkle additional grated Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Pour ingredients into four-quart ice cream freezer.
Stir and freeze.

title: aunt saleemie's coffee cake
directions: Thoroughly grease a large angel food cake pan or extra-long oblong pan (may use 2 loaf pans).

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat until smooth.
Sift cake flour, soda and salt.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk until all ingredients blended well.
Add pecans and coconut and mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in egg whites and vanilla.
Bake in three 8-inch layer cake pans (greased and floured) at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with Italian Cream Cheese Filling.

title: salt water taffy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, salt and water in 2-quart saucepan. Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cook to hard ball stage (260°) without stirring.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Cool until comfortable to handle.
Butter hands; gather taffy into a ball and pull.
When candy is light in color and gets hard to pull, cut in fourths; pull each piece into long strand about 1/2-inch thick.
With buttered scissors, quickly snip in bite-size pieces.
Wrap pieces in wax paper.

title: jello salad
directions: Add 2 cups boiling water to the Jell-O.
Add all ingredients, except the sour cream, to the Jell-O.
Put 1/2 the Jell-O mixture in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator to set.
Remove and spread sour cream over jelled mixture.
Pour rest of Jell-O mixture on top and return to refrigerator.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon.
Pour into ungreased baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Pour icing (recipe follows) over cake while hot.

title: j.o.'s sweet potato pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix potatoes, sugars, spices, salt and flavoring. Add eggs. Combine thoroughly. Stir in pecans and pour into pie shell. Bake 45 minutes. Then reduce heat to 325° and bake additional 10 minutes. Cool and serve.

title: cheesecake
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan with dinner rolls.
Beat together cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add eggs.
Beat well after each egg is added.
Pour in pan over rolls and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Put all in a bowl with pared and sliced apples. Mix well. Set aside while preparing pie pan with crust. Line pie pan with thin rolled crust (top and bottom crust needed). Bake in 400 degree oven for 50 minutes or until lightly brown and apples are tender.

title: asparagus fritters
directions: Drain asparagus.
Mix with flour.
Mix in beaten egg.
Heat 1/4 cup oil.
Drop batter by tablespoons into hot oil.
Turn once.

title: chicken livers
directions: Wash and drain chicken livers.
Pour into a bag.
Flour and add some all seasoned salt.
Add chicken livers and shake to coat. Cook livers in hot oil until done.

title: breakfast pull aparts
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam. Sprinkle nuts in bottom of pan. Put frozen dinner rolls in pan. Pour melted margarine on rolls. Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Sprinkle butterscotch pudding on top. Sprinkle brown sugar on top. Cover with waxed paper. Let set overnight. In the morning, bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: almond cakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil, flour and baking powder; mix well. Add nuts and extract.
Cover in bowl; refrigerate overnight. Take a handful and roll into logs.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until bottom is brown (approximately 20 minutes).
Remove from oven; let cool a few minutes, then cut them diagonally and return to oven until light brown.
Cool, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate chip chewies
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in butter, vanilla and eggs.
Add brown sugar, chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: salmon with creme-fraiche and herb sauce
directions: For the sauce:
In a small bowl combine the creme fraiche, herbs, lemon zest and juice, salt and pepper.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all together, except Cheddar cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cocktail smokies
directions: Heat jelly sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar and mustard.
Simmer slow for 15 minutes.
Add hot dogs and simmer 15 more minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and spread on top of potato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until done.

title: refreshing lackey reunion salad
directions: Mix sugar and buttermilk well.
Add remaining ingredients. Freeze, then serve.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Make vegetables as directed on package (use frozen vegetables); drain.
Vegetables must be made separately.
Place cauliflower on bottom of 4-quart casserole.
Place 1/2 onion rings on next; put all of broccoli on next.
Spread all of cheese over the top; stir soups together and pour over cheese.
Add rest of onion rings on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: herbed crusted fish
directions: Brush fillets with olive oil.
Blend croutons and herbs to fine consistency in food processor.
Coat fish on both sides with bread crumbs.
Place on roasting rack in oven and roast at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Heat egg, milk, salt and pepper, celery seed and yellow food coloring in saucepan.
Cut Velveeta into bite size pieces.
Layer macaroni, cheese and sauce.
Put butter on top. Bake at 425° until brown on top.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain liquid from beets.
Place beets in jar.
Bring to a boil the sugar and vinegar until dissolved.
Pour over beets.
Cover and put in the refrigerator.
Will keep for weeks.

title: jelly roll
directions: Line a greased pan (9 x 13-inch) with wax paper and grease that.
Beat the eggs 5 minutes, beat in gradually the sugar, beat in all at once the vanilla and water.
Sift the dry ingredients together and add all at once, being careful not to beat longer than necessary, and pour into pan.
When baked, turn upside down immediately on a cloth sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Cut edges of cake so that it won't split when rolled.
Spread immediately with jelly and roll.
If you use cloth to roll with it won't split as easily.
Wrap in towel until cool.
They freeze well too.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup warm water and set aside.
Mix egg, potato, sugar, salt and shortening together.
Add flour gradually to mixture.
Add dissolved yeast to other ingredients and knead until smooth.
Put dough in greased bowl and let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Work down and repeat rising process. Make rolls and cook in 400° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: freezer potato rolls
directions: Cook potato in boiling water to cover for 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup liquid; set potato aside.
Cool reserved liquid before adding yeast and sugar.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook chopped green pepper and chopped onion until tender.
Add hamburger and tomato soup, salt and pepper.
Cook spaghetti and pour sauce over it.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken mac bake
directions: Combine 1 cup cheese and remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts and salt.
Microwave 5 1/2 to 6 minutes. Add butter, vanilla and baking soda.
Stir just to mix and melt butter (mixture will be foamy, do not stir down).
Pour onto a well buttered cookie sheet.
Tilt pan to spread mixture.
When cool, break into small pieces.

title: cinnamon bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, oil and eggs.
Place 1 1/2 cups of mix in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over mixture. Add remaining cake mix.
With knife swirl cake mix and cinnamon.
Mix.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until middle is done.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat; add onion and saute until tender.
Stir in hominy and remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour mixture in baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake another 5 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer into casserole the broccoli, cheese and crumbs.
Do the layering once more. Bake for 25 minutes at 350° in a covered casserole.

title: spiced wild duck
directions: Rub each duck well inside and out with salt, pepper and ground ginger.
Place one-half apple in each duck; place ducks in a large baking pan.
In a skillet, saute onions in butter until lightly browned; add water and vinegar and heat to boiling.
Add remaining ingredients and remove from heat; pour mixture over ducks.
Start cooking at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for approximately 2 hours, basting frequently.

title: sour cream or yogurt peach torte
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and 1/4 cup sugar.
Cut in 3/4 cup butter (if butter is cold, use electric mixer until crumb consistency).
Next, press this mixture into a deep 9 or 10-inch pie plate by using a smaller pie plate to press with.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix eggs, corn, sour cream, meal, peppers and oil.
Pour 1/2 batter in 9-inch square pan and add 1/2 cup of cheese.
Pour rest of batter and add cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Baking time may vary.
Serves 8.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Beat eggs and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well with mixer. Place in 2 bread pans (well-greased and floured).
You can use four 3 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch pans, if you want smaller loaves.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chuck roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with Lawry's salt.
Using medium heat, brown the roast on both sides in 2 tablespoons oil (Mazola or Crisco). Spread the mushroom soup on top of the roast, then sprinkle the onion soup mix on top.
Put lid on and cook 1 1/2 hours using medium or low heat.
Your gravy will be made and ready to eat.

title: cheese and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook 1/2 pound of macaroni noodles in salt water for approximately 15 minutes.
Spray a 1 1/2 quart baking dish with Pam.
Drain noodles.
Put a layer of noodles first then sliced sharp Cheddar cheese.
Follow this procedure with cheese being the top layer.
Place bits of margarine on top of each layer of cheese. Add milk until it appears above the last layer of macaroni noodles.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rolled and stuffed flank steak
directions: Saute onions with seasonings in hot oil for 2 to 3 minutes. Add bread crumbs and celery leaves.
Mix thoroughly.
Pound flank steak with a mallet.
Spread stuffing on meat.
Roll meat lengthwise like a jelly roll and tie securely in 4 or 5 places. Place roll on rack in a baking dish.
Roast at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Serve on platter.
Remove strings and carve diagonally across the grain of the meat.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops; set aside.
Melt margarine in oblong pan. Add soup, broth and rice in pan.
Place chops in pan on top of mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute meat; drain. Add other ingredients, except Fritos, 1 chopped onion and cheese. Use Fritos, onion and cheese in greased casserole dish. Layer ingredients,
start with Fritos and end with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Cook the vermicelli and drain.
Marinate overnight in the lemon juice, Accent and oil.
The next day, add the remaining ingredients and chill.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and take off bone. Saute onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic. Mix soups, Ro-Tel with juice, 1 cup chicken broth, Velveeta and chicken. Add seasonings. Simmer about 1 hour. Serve over cooked vermicelli.

title: tropical twist
directions: Place
all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth. Yield: 4 servings.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix the cauliflower, onion, broccoli and eggs together. Combine together the mayonnaise, oil, vinegar, sugar and bacon bits and pour over salad and refrigerate.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well, then add baby food, raisins and nuts.
Stir together. Bake in sheet pan at 375° for 30 minutes. Bake extra 5 minutes if raisins or nuts are used.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Thoroughly mix with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and serve with crackers (Town House or Escort are great).
Double recipe for a crowd.

title: hash browns casserole
directions: Pour into long, greased cake pan.
Top with crackers mixed with margarine.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and beginning to brown. With a toothpick, test a bit of potato.
If not quite done or if casserole is still too soupy, return to oven until golden brown. It will thicken as it cools.

title: baked fish
directions: Wash fish with lemon juice.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers. Sprinkle with garlic, onion and parsley; dot with butter.
Fold over so it is evenly coated.
Sprinkle with more stuffing, lemon juice and butter dots.
Bake at 500° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Put into greased loaf pan or dish.
Bake in a moderately hot 375° oven for 1 hour. You may serve hot or cold.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan combine the sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Cook over medium heat until the mixture reaches the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until thick and no longer glossy. Pour into a buttered dish or plate.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll into small balls.
Dip in 12 ounces melted chocolate chips.
Cool on wax paper.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread in 8-inch square pan apples. Sprinkle with a mixture of water, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Work together until crumbly, using pastry blender sugar, sifted flour and butter.
Spread crumb mixture over apples.
Bake uncovered about 40 minutes.
Serve warm with rich milk.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef, onions and peppers. Drain grease.
Add mushrooms and pizza sauce.
Pour in 8-inch casserole dish.
Top with cheese and place in oven to melt cheese. While melting, mix Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Pour this on top of meat and cheese.
Place back in oven.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato-vegetable casserole
directions: Brown the ground chuck in a skillet; drain off fat.
Boil the mixed vegetables for 6 to 8 minutes.
Mix all ingredients with the browned meat and cooked mixed vegetables and place in a casserole or a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until nicely browned.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Place warm water in large mixing bowl.
Sprinkle dry yeast over warm water; let set for 3 minutes.
Add cake mix, 1 cup flour, eggs, oil and salt.
Beat with mixer until bubbles appear. Add flour and stir.
Makes a soft dough.
Knead on well-floured board, put in bowl and let rise until doubled in size.
Divide dough, roll out and spread with margarine, sugar and cinnamon. Roll up, cut and place on greased pan.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Ice while hot with powdered sugar icing.

title: baked breakfast burritos
directions: *Add sour cream and enchilada/taco sauce to serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute celery in butter to make it tender.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook for 20 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Put yeast in very warm water.
Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in greased muffin tins.

title: red lentil soup(makes 6 servings)
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, heat olive oil.
Add onion, celery and carrot; saute until onion is transparent.
Stir in lentils; heat to boiling.
Cook over high heat until liquid is almost evaporated.
Stir in water, chili powder, bay leaf, thyme, salt, pepper, allspice and cumin.
Heat mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in tomato and green onions; continue to cook 15 minutes longer or until lentils are tender.

title: date bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; grease bread or loaf pan.
Check dates to be sure no kernels in dates; bring dates to boil in water.
Add soda, shortening and nuts.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Put in bread pan and bake 1 hour.
Serve plain or with softened cream cheese.

title: spinach spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill several hours or overnight. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Melt chocolate	and margarine over hot water.
Put egg, cream, vanilla and
sugar	in a bowl to beat well.
Add chocolate mixture;
beat
with mixer enough to blend.
Add nuts, if desired. Pour
in
buttered
dish
and place in refrigerator. Cut when firm.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In a small saucepan, brown onion lightly in margarine over low heat.
In a large bowl, combine meat, rolled oats, egg, seasonings and cooked onion.
With floured hands, shape meat into small balls.
Fry slowly in 3 tablespoons of margarine until brown, turning often.
Remove when browned.
Add the soup and water to drippings in skillet; stir until smooth and bubbly.
Return meatballs to soup mixture in skillet.
Cover tightly and simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.
Serve at once or cool.
Chill and reheat the next day.
May also be frozen.

title: scripture bars
directions: Beat Jeremiah 17:11 until light.
Add Jeremiah 6:20 and Psalm 55:21; blend well.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well and pour into a greased 6 x 10-inch cake pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Cut into 24 bars and roll in pulverized Jeremiah 6:20.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in crock-pot on low. Cook for 3 1/2 hours.

title: mexican goulash
directions: Fry hamburger until done; drain and add all other ingredients. Cook until done.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Coat chicken breasts with flour and seasoned salt.
Saute chicken with oleo and oil, adding more if needed.
Transfer cooked breasts to a platter.
Squeeze lemon juice over them.
Keep warm until served.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a 9 inch x 12 inch greased baking dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Prepare cornmeal by adding egg and oil and pour into a cake pan.
Cook until brown.
Take corn bread out and crumble in a large bowl.
Chop onion; add to corn bread.
Add chicken broth and garlic salt.
Stir thoroughly.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream
together
butter,
lard
and sugar.
Add egg and molasses
and beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger, clove
and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Add hot water and beat until smooth.
The batter is soft but it makes a fine cake. Bake in greased shallow pan 35 minutes at 325°.
Yields 10 servings.

title: vegetable beef stew
directions: Stir-fry cubed beef lightly.

In a large pan, add the tomatoes, peas, lima beans, potatoes, cut onion and cut carrots. Cook on medium for 45 minutes. Add the oil, hot pepper and salt. Stir and cook 15 minutes. Add stir-fry beef and cook 30 minutes until done.

title: easy homemade fudge
directions: Mix condensed milk and chocolate chips in a saucepan.
Heat over medium-low heat until chocolate chips are melted.
Mix in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: corn pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.

title: beef gumbo soup
directions: Cut beef in small pieces and brown in oil.
Add salt and 2 quarts water and onion.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Add carrots, potatoes, celery and garlic powder.
Cook 30 minutes longer.
Add tomatoes, beans, lima beans, corn and cabbage.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add okra and heat.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Mix the cup of boiling water with the lemon gelatin and then add the cream cheese to it, beating it into the gelatin a little at a time with the electric mixer.
Add the pineapple, pecans, sugar, vanilla and 7-Up.
Then add the green food coloring.
Put this into your refrigerator and let stand.
When it begins to set, mix it again so the pecans won't come to the top.

title: butter dips
directions: Heat oven to 450° (hot). Melt butter in oven in oblong pan, 13 x 9 1/2-inches. Remove from oven when butter is melted. Sift dry ingredients into bowl. Add milk. Stir slowly with fork until dough just clings together (about 30 strokes). Turn out on well floured board; knead lightly about 10 minutes. Roll out 1/2-inch thick into rectangle, 8 x 12-inches. Cut in half lengthwise, then crosswise into 16 strips. Dip each strip on both sides in melted butter. Place close together in 2 rows in pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown. Serve piping hot. Makes 32 Butter Dips.

title: easy strawberry cake
directions: Cut up the strawberries in a large bowl. Put sugar on strawberries and place in icebox overnight to allow juice to form. When strawberries are ready, bake cake and allow to cool. Place 1 layer of cake in bottom of large bowl. Poke holes in top of cake and put some juice on top of cake. Place Cool Whip on top of cake. Put second layer on top of first layer. Repeat same step. Pour strawberries and juice around cake. Cover and place in icebox until ready to eat. Lasts about 3 days.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp; keep juice.
Mix shrimp (chopped fine) with cream cheese.
Add 2 teaspoons of Worcestershire sauce and 5 drops of Tabasco sauce; blend as desired.

title: grape juice
directions: Place washed, stemmed grapes and sugar in a 1-quart jar.
Fill with boiling water.
Process by a home canning method.
Let set for 2 months.
When ready, strain into a pitcher and add cold water to taste.

title: plantation supper
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add corn, noodles, salt and pepper.
Mix together milk, cream of mushroom soup and cream cheese.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops
directions: In a bag, put the flour, garlic salt, celery salt, seasoned salt and paprika.
Shake pork chops in the flour mixture, then brown them slowly in 2 tablespoons fat.
While they brown, slice bell pepper.
Put a ring on each pork chop.
Put half apple on top of the green pepper slices.
Mix water, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over the apples.
Simmer, covered, being sure it doesn't boil, for 40 minutes.

title: spinach fondondo
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Add the spinach; cover pan and cook until thawed.
Add the soup and sour cream; mix thoroughly.
Transfer to buttered casserole.
Arrange sliced cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken with figs
directions: Use drained juices to gently cook chicken in a large skillet (with salt and pepper).
Remove chicken to warm bowl and cook the juices until thickened.
Remove from heat, after 5 minutes, and gently add sour cream, stirring quickly.
Add lemon juice, vanilla, figs and pineapple.
Pour over the chicken and stir. Sprinkle toasted sesame seed over all.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: cold-curing-hot chili
directions: In a large chili pot, fry the bacon.
Remove the bacon and reserve the drippings.
Brown the stew meat in the bacon drippings.
Add the chopped onions and cook until clear.
Add the habanero peppers.
(These peppers are extremely hot.
For a milder taste, use jalapenos.)
Stir frequently.
Add the undrained tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Simmer for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Note:
Any other vegetables on hand may be added.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine crumbs, 2 tablespoons Parmesan, oregano, garlic powder and pepper.
Roll chicken parts in crumb mixture; arrange in 2-quart shallow baking dish, 12 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken dish
directions: Place slices of lean corned beef on bottom of greased dish. Wrap a slice of bacon around boneless chicken breast and place on beef slice.
Spoon sour cream over each piece.
Pour cream of mushroom soup (add a little water) over all.
Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: orange sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Put in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rich hot chocolate
directions: Microwave milk on 100% power for about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. Add remaining ingredients to container and mix until chips are melted.
Serve right away and enjoy.

title: peon pie
directions: Brown beef and onions in skillet.
Add green chilies and cook 10 minutes.
Add seasonings to taste.
Add soup and milk; simmer for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: taco appetizer
directions: Open cans of refried beans. In bowl mix avocado, lemon juice, 4 tablespoons mayonnaise, salt and pepper, set aside, In another bowl mix 1/2 cup mayonnaise, 1 cup sour cream and taco seasoning mix and set aside. Layer on a very large plate as follows:

title: no crust pie
directions: Beat all ingredients.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes its own crust.

title: nanny's pecan pie
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter.
Add and beat well the next three ingredients.
Add pecans and pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: chicken divan
directions: In a greased casserole dish, layer cooked broccoli, then the chicken.
Mix mayonnaise, milk, soup and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve over cooked rice.

title: chocolate triple layer pie
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on packages. Spoon 1 1/2 cups of pudding into pie crust and smooth out. Gently stir 1/2 Cool Whip into remaining pudding.
Spread over first pudding layer. Top with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Garnish as desired.

title: hello dollies or magic squares
directions: Layer ingredients in order.
Pour can of Eagle Brand milk over top and cook at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Combine in blender or with mixer until smooth.
If blended to long it will get very thick.
Just add a little hot water to thin. This equals one can of eagle brand milk.

title: harvest pecan cake
directions: Have butter at room temperature.
Sift dry ingredients. Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Beat egg yolks in large bowl.
Cream together butter and brown sugar.
Add yolks.
Mix well.
Combine milk, vanilla and dissolved coffee. Add dry ingredients to brown sugar and butter mixture alternately with liquid, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add pecans and fold in egg whites.
Bake in tube pan sprayed with Pam or greased and floured in preheated oven at 325°.
Place in pan of water on bottom rack to prevent overbrowning.
If cake browns too fast, place piece of foil on top.
Bake for about 1 hour.
Needs no frosting but you can if you want it.

title: boiled peanuts
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil; simmer 4 to 5 hours.
Cool 30 minutes; drain and refrigerate.
(May be frozen to use at a later date.)

title: strained baby food plum cake
directions: Mix ingredients
in order given.
Bake in Bundt pan in a 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: leftover turkey
directions: Scoop out bread, leaving 1/2-inch on sides and bottom.
Brush with melted butter on top and sides of bread.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Serve as a dip for vegetables.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger and season with cumin. Add onions.
Drain.
Spray casserole dish with Pam or a similar product.
Line dish with tortillas.
Add hamburger/onion mixture.

title: cranberry citrus sparkler
directions: Place 1 tablespoon lime juice into each glass. Combine ice cubes, water and cranberry juice concentrate in 5-cup blender container. Cover; blend at high speed until ice cubes are finely chopped (20 to 30 seconds). Pour about 2/3 cup cranberry mixture and 1/3 cup sparkling water into each glass. Garnish with lime slices. Makes 8 (8-ounce) servings.

title: sixty minute dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Combine milk, water and margarine.
Heat until very warm (margarine does not need to melt).
Add to dry ingredients and mix with electric mixer (medium speed) 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup flour and mix (high speed) 2 more minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface and knead until smooth, about 5 to 6 minutes. Cover and let rest 15 minutes.
Shape dough into rolls and place in greased baking dish.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen rolls.

title: cream tacos
directions: Heat chili, beans and Ro-Tel tomatoes together.
Add cheese and coffee creamer or Cool Whip.
Serve over Fritos.

title: parsley new potatoes
directions: 1 Hot Dog:
Cook on High for 50 to 60 seconds.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and roll into small balls.
Cook in 350° oven until golden brown.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Can freeze what is not needed.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello, orange juice and hot water until dissolved.
Add pineapple, nuts, celery and cranberry sauce.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Keep refrigerated.

title: crullers doughnuts
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Roll and cut out the doughnuts.
Let rise 1 hour before deep frying.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. In a shallow bowl, combine the next 6 ingredients. Dredge chicken in butter, then in crumb mixture. Place chicken in the baking dish with skin side up and thick edges toward the outside. Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture. Arrange on rack in broiler pan. Bake in 425° oven 40 to 45 minutes or until tender and juices run clear and chicken is no longer pink. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach and tear into pieces.
Toss spinach, bean sprouts and water chestnuts together.
Garnish with egg and bacon.

title: grandma's coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburg and drain well.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer for 2 hours or until juice is cooked down.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Set aside.
Cut horizontally through pork chops almost to bone.
Stuff with stuffing, then secure with toothpicks.

title: cheese swirls
directions: Stir biscuit mix and milk until dough follows fork around bowl.
Turn out on floured surface.
Roll out dough; sprinkle with cheese.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Seal edge.
Cut in 1/2-inch thick slices and bake at 350° until browned.

title: cherry wink cookies
directions: Mix and drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Thin with sweet milk and bake slow.

title: deep south chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion, drain.
Add other ingredients and cook 1 hour on low heat.

title: jello shots
directions: Make Jell-O as directions on box, then add 1/2 cup of cold water and 3/4 cup of liquor.
Mix well together; pour into 1 or 2 ounce Dixie cups.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: tomato bisque
directions: Cook over medium heat 10 minutes, stirring often.

title: individual chicken pies
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender; blend in flour and seasonings.
Stir in broth.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Add chicken, vegetables and pimiento; heat until bubbly.
Pour into 6 individual casseroles.
Quarter biscuits; place 8 pieces atop hot filling in each casserole.
Bake at 450° unti lightly browned, 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Place sugar, oil, eggs, salt, flour, baking soda, cinnamon and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Beat with wooden spoon or use electric mixer until ingredients are well blended.
Add apples, half of nuts and raisins and blend.
Turn batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar before serving.

title: tarragon chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium sized bowl and chill.
Serve on whole wheat rolls or in pita bread.

title: bob's argentine boiled dinner
directions: Boil 4 quarts of water with ribs, chicken and salted pork for 2 1/2 hours. Add sausages, carrots and turnips.
Boil 1 more hour. Add rest of the ingredients and boil 1/2 hour more.
Serve meat surrounded by vegetables.
Liquid can be used for soup.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add rest of ingredients and stir hard.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Also can top with Cheddar cheese.

title: panda bear bread
directions: Beat shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs, then beat in applesauce and pumpkin.
Stir together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, mace, nutmeg and cloves.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture, stir until flour is moist; then stir in apricots, dates and nuts. Put into 2 greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: caramel-chocolate squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat caramels and 1/4 cup milk in a saucepan
over
medium heat, stirring constantly, until melted and mixture
is
smooth.
Keep
warm
over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Mix dry cake mix, margarine, remaining milk and pecans.
Spread
half the dough (1 1/2 cups) into an ungreased rectangular
x
9 x 2-inch) pan.
Bake 6 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with chocolate chips and coconut.
Drizzle caramel
mixture over chips and coconut.
Drop remaining dough by spoonfuls over caramel layer and spread evenly.
Bake until slightly
dry
to
touch
(15 to 20 minutes, or longer).
Cool completely,
then
refrigerate
until
firm.
Cut into 2 1/2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 48.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine with sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.

title: aunt mollie's chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender, falling off the bone.
Separate chicken from bone.
Save soup stock for something else.
Thaw crusts while boiling chicken.
Saute in oil, celery and onion. Cook carrots in microwave 15 minutes with lots of water.
Drain celery, onion and carrots.
Combine with deboned chicken and cream of mushroom soup.
Heat through in saucepan.
Pour into lower pie crust.
Cover with 2nd crust.
Prick holes in your favorite pattern.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, eggs and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Roll in small balls, then dip in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Bake until lightly browned, but still soft.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish.

title: purple salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple; save 1/4 cup juice of cherries. Cream the cheese and add juice.
Combine cream cheese and other ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Serve in glass bowl.

title: baked catfish
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place fish in baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over it.
Sprinkle potato chips and cheese generously over top of fish.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Heat milk in top of double boiler.
Add rice, sugar and salt. Stir occasionally.
Add raisins when rice is tender.
Heat a few minutes without stirring or raisins will color the rice.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 2 well-oiled bread pans.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: creamy cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in small pieces.
Season and simmer in small amount of water until tender.
Add sour cream and cheese and serve immediately.

title: buckwheat bread
directions: Combine shortening, honey, salt and milk.
Add cold water and yeast.
Gradually add buckwheat flour and white flour.
Knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise in warm place 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Place on board and divide into 2 parts. Let rise 15 minutes.
Shape into loaves and place in greased pans. Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sour cream crescents
directions: Cut butter into flour until particles
are the size of a pea. Add yolk and sour cream.
Mix well and chill 1 hour.

title: chunky onion dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order in an oblong glass dish.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Line a 9-inch pan with one crust.
In mixing bowl, mix well the apples, sugar, salt, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Place apples in pan.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with lemon.
Top with remaining crust which has been pricked.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until done.
May lightly sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon before putting in oven.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place sliced lettuce in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add in layers the celery, green pepper, onions and peas.
Spread mayonnaise over peas.
Sprinkle mayonnaise layer with sugar, then sprinkle cheese over top.
Cook bacon until crispy; drain.
Break bacon into bits or use Bac*Os.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
Cut in squares to serve.
Can be kept in fridge for several days.

title: never fail banana bread
directions: Mix up a batch of your favorite homemade biscuits.
Roll out to about 1 inch thick.
Over dough sprinkle 2 to 3 grated apples, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up like jelly roll and slice. Place slices on deep cookie pan and pour 3 cups of hot water that has 1 cup white sugar dissolved in it.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Core and clean peppers.
Leave whole.
Parboil 5 minutes. Brown meat and onion in fat.
Add tomatoes, rice, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer until rice is almost tender.
Add cheese.
Stuff peppers and stand upright in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 320° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with more cheese; let melt.

title: chicken breasts with balsamic vinegar
directions: Add pepper to flour.
Dredge chicken and saute in olive oil until lightly brown on both sides.
Remove.
Add garlic, mushrooms and bay leaf to skillet.
Add vinegar and broth.
Scrape up bits and reduce heat.
Put chicken back into pan and cover.
Simmer for 5 to 8 minutes, turning chicken once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Dip chicken cubes in egg, then crumbs. Brown in oil.
Put in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pour broth over chicken and add mushrooms. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peter's rarebit
directions: Sprinkle tomato slices with sugar, salt and pepper; broil on both sides and keep warm.
Saute the bacon.
Drain and keep warm. Melt the butter in a double boiler over simmering water.
Add mustards, Worcestershire, paprika, Tabasco and blend.
Add cheese. Allow most to melt, stirring frequently.
Add beer and continue stirring until the cheese is completely melted.
Beat the egg yolks with the cream and add slowly to the cheese mixture, stirring until thickened, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, toast the split muffins.
Layer the tomatoes and bacon on the muffins and spoon the thickened sauce over all.
Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: date muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and applesauce.
Mix well. Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Mix well.
Add dates and walnuts.
Bake in cupcake pan at 375° until done.

title: homemade eggrolls
directions: Brown meat and drain.
In large skillet, add cabbage, carrots, onion, beans and soy sauce.
Cook until vegetables are tender. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place 2 tablespoons of vegetables per wrapper.
Roll up and deep fry eggroll until they slightly brown.

title: chocolate dr. pepper cake
directions: Heat fat and Dr. Pepper. Sift together flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and cocoa. Combine eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla. Add hot Dr. Pepper mixture to dry ingredients (blend well). Add egg mixture. Mix well. Pour in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and stir until melted and smooth.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Form into balls and return to refrigerator for 2 hours.
Melt chocolate morsels.
Take a toothpick and dip each ball into melted chocolate.
Put on wax paper until set.
Store in refrigerator.

title: potato-tomato bake
directions: In casserole, layer potatoes and onions in alternate layers until full.
Pour the stewed tomatoes over top; dot with butter. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.

title: old time tea cake "cookies"
directions: In large bowl, add sugar and Crisco (room temp).
Blend with spoon by hand.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each egg. Then add milk and vanilla.
Mix real good by hand.
Add flour and baking powder sifted together.
Pat dough on a cloth with flour and roll out as thin as you want;
cut with round cookie cutter. Bake at 350 degrees till light brown.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Remove tips from wings.
Cut into 2 pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken, marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Remove chicken from marinade and place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour or until lightly brown, basting occasionally with marinade.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Whisk until smooth.
When using for Mountain Burger sauce, make slightly thicker.

title: e z gumbo
directions: Combine okra, tomatoes, rice and water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer about 5 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: With electric mixer, add sugar gradually to eggs. Continue until very thick (almost like cake batter). Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Put in gallon freezer and freeze. Can add frozen strawberries or other flavors before freezing.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, water and sugar together.
Stir until sugar melts.
Add lemonade, orange juice and pineapple juice to mixture and stir well.
Pour extra punch into mold and freeze.
Yield:
3 gallons.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix 1 can of tomato sauce and all the other ingredients together.
Put into an oiled 5 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Refrigerate for 20 minutes to set.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.
Take out and pour other can of tomato sauce on top and return to oven and cook an additional 20 minutes longer.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes; rinse and chop.
Cook until tender and water is almost cooked away.
Drain remaining water.
Salt and pepper. Mash the potatoes a little.
Add milk.

title: garden chicken
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in 10-inch skillet until tender but not browned.
Add chicken. Brown on both sides, 2 to 3 minutes per side.

Sprinkle with sage, thyme, salt and pepper. Cut up tomatoes. Add with juice and wine to skillet. Cut asparagus into 2-inch pieces. Sprinkle over chicken mixture. Reduce heat and cook, covered, 30 minutes.
Remove chicken and vegetables to serving platter. Thicken juices, if desired.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with parsley. Serve with grated Romano cheese, if desired.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from stove.
Add raisins, vinegar, butter, jar of jelly and spices. Mix well and put on stove.
Add cornstarch to thicken to desired consistency.

title: any cake mix cookies
directions: Melt butter; add egg and cake mix, mixing together.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown and season meat.
In separate dish, mix soup and liquid. Use baking dish.
Put layer of Tots, meat, then soup.
Repeat with a few Tots on top.
Cover with foil and bake for 15 minutes at 275° to 300°.
Uncover and continue to bake 10 to 15 minutes until Tots are soft.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
In bowl mix flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and ginger.
With pastry blender cut in margarine until coarse crumbs.
Stir in quick oats and walnuts. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken dorito casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cook and debone chicken.
Combine onion, chicken, soups and tomatoes.
Layer in casserole:
Doritos, then chicken combination and then cheese.
Repeat layers and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: shrdlu dew
directions: If you're like the guy who couldn't afford to drown his troubles over the high cost of living, hark to Shrdlu's recipe for do-it-yourself wine at $.89 a gallon.
You'll need a 1 gallon jug, sterilized, 1 cake of yeast, crumbled ($.09), 4 cups of sugar ($.25), 1 large can frozen grape juice ($.45) and 1 large balloon ($.10).
Put yeast, sugar and grape juice into jug and fill with water.
Slip the balloon over mouth of jug, sealing the contents from the atmosphere.
During fermentation, the balloon will inflate.
When it deflates, the wine is ready.
The process takes 6 weeks and produces a clear rosy beverage that tastes like pink Catawba.
Shrdlu points out that if you re-use the balloon, the next gallon will cost only $.79.

title: derrick kegley's applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and sides of 10-inch tube pan.
Heat applesauce and soda; set aside to cool.
Toss dates and raisins with 2 tablespoons of the flour.
In large bowl, combine dry ingredients with mixer at medium speed, slowly adding applesauce and margarine.
When mixture is smooth, fold in raisins, nuts, dates and coconut.
Turn into pan and bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: cooked slaw dressing
directions: Cook together until thickened. Cool. Use over slaw or lettuce and green onions. Stir constantly while cooking. Sprinkle in celery seed.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Combine hamburger, peas and 1 cup cheese.
Put into browned pie shells.
Put equal amount of potatoes on top of mixture.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top of pies.
Bake at 350° until cheese has melted.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Put in bowl the sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla. Stir or beat just enough to mix well.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour, powdered sugar and butter.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar, lemon juice and baking powder.
Pour over crust.
Bake another 25 minutes.
When done, sprinkle powdered sugar over top while hot.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix gelatin, water, pineapple and blueberry pie filling and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate until firm.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Mix all ingredients except steak.
Marinate steak in marinade overnight.
Grill to desired doneness.

title: easy french chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Melt chocolate; let cool.
Stir chocolate into butter-sugar mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each on high speed.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into prepared pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Store in refrigerator.

title: shanghai casserole
directions: Saute onions in shortening.
Remove from pan; brown pork and veal.
Add soy sauce and onion salt.
Pour hot water over meat; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add diced celery; simmer for 15 minutes. Add all vegetables.
Combine cornstarch and water into smooth paste; add to mixture, stirring, until clear.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 27 minutes.
Top with onion biscuit topping.

title: snickerdoodle drops
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In a large bowl beat together butter, brown sugar and 3/4 cup granulated sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and mix well. In medium bowl, combine flour, oats, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add to sugar mixture.
Mix well. Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto prepared cookie sheet.
In a small bowl, combine remaining 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Sprinkle lightly over each cookie. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire cooling rack.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add other ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot on low for a few hours.
Serve with "Mexican Salad."

title: reese's peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugars together. Add eggs, peanut butter, milk and vanilla. Add flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet. Top the cookies with Reese's peanut butter cups cut into pieces. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions and carrots in oil in saucepan until brown.
Add water, bouillon cubes and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in broccoli and noodles.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add milk and cheese. Cook until cheese melts.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: savory seafood bisque
directions: Cook mushrooms, green onions and scallops in 1/4 cup butter until seafood is translucent. Add flour and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add chunky salsa and simmer 2 minutes. Add milk, stirring constantly. Add cooked crabmeat and shrimp. Add Frito-Lay cheese dip. Do not boil.
Serve immediately. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Bake in tube pan only.

title: low-fat banana muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In a separate bowl, combine beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and balance of ingredients. Spray (12-count) muffin pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Kraft barbecue sauce gives this recipe real cookout flavor.

title: spicy broccoli soup
directions: Saute chopped onion in oleo.
Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain broccoli. Place onion, broccoli and rest of ingredients in saucepan on top of stove.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring often, until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook celery and onions 15 minutes.
Add potatoes, parsley, onion powder, garlic powder and pepper. Cook until potatoes are soft.
Mix together flour and evaporated milk.
Beat in egg and add.
Stir until thick.
Salt to taste.
May have to add more water.

title: rene's famous spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in large skillet, stirring until crumbled.
Add
remaining ingredients with enough water to thin to desired consistency.
Mix well.
Simmer for 1 hour. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: lemon cream fruit dip
directions: In small bowl, beat eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice until foamy.
In medium saucepan, combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually add water; mix well.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened and clear; remove from heat. Gradually beat in egg mixture.
Over low heat, cook and stir until slightly thickened; add vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold in the whipping cream.
Chill. Serve with fresh fruit. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: the world's richest cheesecake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together in a medium size bowl.
Cut in butter or margarine with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Add egg yolk and vanilla.
Mix lightly with fork just until pastry holds together and leaves side of bowl clean.
Chill until ready to use.

title: poor man's steak
