directions: Chill several hours in fridge.
Form into hamburger patties. Flour both sides and fry in skillet until well browned on both sides.
Put in a casserole dish.
Add 1 can mushroom soup and 1 cup milk.
Pour over hamburgers.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tabouli salad
directions: Pour the bulgur into a large bowl; mix well with olive oil, lemon juice and water.
Let stand.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Combine milk, margarine, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast and stir.
Add eggs.
Gradually stir in flour.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Divide into three portions.
Roll each portion into a 9-inch circle.
Cut circle into 12 wedges.
Beginning at outer edge, roll up and place seam side down on a greased pan.
Allow plenty of space between each roll. Brush with additional butter.
Cover and let rise.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
These freeze well.
Let rise, then shape into rolls.
Freeze on a piece of aluminum foil.
Put in plastic bag. Take out as needed.
Let thaw and rise, then bake.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Scald milk; add shortening and sugar and stir until dissolved.
Dissolve yeast in water.
When milk has cooled, add 1 cup flour and stir until smooth.
Add yeast and egg; beat well.
Add flour gradually until dough becomes stiff enough to knead with hand and has a satin like finish.
Place in a greased bowl; cover with a clean damp towel and place in the refrigerator until the next day or set in a warm place and let rise until double in size.
Form into rolls.
Let rise again until double in size.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine ingredients in a greased casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven approximately 1 hour.
Top will be puffed and nicely browned.

title: italian chicken
directions: Cut 2 packages boneless chicken breasts into bit size pieces. Shake pieces in a plastic bag with flour.
Add to 4 beaten eggs. Soak in beaten eggs over night in the refrigerator.
Remove from egg and roll in Italian bread crumbs.
Saute in butter.
Place in a casserole; add to drippings 1 cup chicken broth, 1/2 cup wine, optional.
Pour over chicken.
Top with 1/2 lb sliced mushrooms. Add 3/4 lb grated Muenster cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: hamburger and peppers
directions: Cook hamburger, onion, celery, garlic, salt and pepper until brown.
Add remaining ingredients, cook until peppers are done. Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until blended.
Add egg and beat until blended. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with fork.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes before removing from baking sheet. Yields 3 dozen.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread	pineapple
over
bottom
of
9	x
13-inch pan. Spread cherry
filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pie filling.
Sprinkle	nuts
over cake mix.
Cut butter into pats and cover top completely.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar; cut in shortening.
Beat egg; add vinegar and water and sprinkle a little at a time over flour mixture.
Mix.
Gather dough together with hands so it cleans the bowl; knead very lightly.
Chill before rolling.
Makes enough for 6 crusts.

title: cream cheese breakfast roll
directions: The next day mix all ingredients.
Cut dough in 4 pieces; roll out to dinner plate size.
Spread 1/4 cream cheese mixture over 1 piece of rolled out dough.
Roll it up.
Seal all seams and ends. Put seam on bottom.
Put on greased pan.
Let rise to double size, then bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Frost with icing.
Repeat for other 3 pieces of dough.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Chop nuts, oranges and cranberries in food processor or chopper. Add two cups sugar, mix well. Mix water and Jello, let cool until thick. Add fruit and nut mixture. Chill until set. This keeps well and is even better the next day.

title: brown sugar caramel
directions: Mix all ingredients excluding vanilla and nuts in 6-quart pot. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture reaches hard ball stage.
(I use cold tap water and drip off spoon.)
You should be able to mold it with your fingers.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch buttered pan; cool and cut.

title: broccoli haters broccoli
directions: In heavy 12-inch skillet, heat olive oil for 1 minute.
Add onion, garlic, water, broccoli, pepper, oregano and pepper flakes. Cook, stirring, for about 2 minutes.
Cover skillet, reduce heat to low and cook 8 to 9 minutes longer, stirring often until tender, but crisp.
Serves 4. Nutrition information per serving:
7 grams fat; 16 calories; 0 cholesterol and 39 mg sodium.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat eggs and mix with remaining ingredients.
Put into a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding; chill overnight.
Add remaining ingredients.
Keep cold.

title: marinated pea salad
directions: Combine beans, peas, pimentos, celery, and onion.
Mix last 5 ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Chill over night and drain before serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425° to 450°.
Cut the biscuits in fourths, roll and cover them with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake for about 10 minutes.
Melt the butter and add cinnamon and sugar mixture to butter.
Pour over biscuits.
Put back in oven for about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese flan
directions: Mix the sugar and water in a deep, ovenproof glass dish.
Place dish in oven for 8 to 10 minutes, until caramel forms.
Let caramel cool.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in a blender for a few minutes (blend in the cream cheese last).
Pour mixture in glass dish which contains the caramel.
Bake in oven for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: flag cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9 pan, line with wax paper.
Grease again.
Sift Flour, baking powder and salt and set aside.
In another bowl, beat eggs and add sugar and extracts.
Scald milk and add to dry ingredients.
Add egg mixture.
Pour into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.
When done, let cool in pan at least 30 minutes.
Whip the cream and add confectioners sugar and vanilla. Slice the strawberries.
Slice cake lengthwise.
Take 1 1/2 cups of frosting mixture and add strawberries (reserve enough for garnish) and spread for filling.
Add top layer and frost with remaining cream.
With remaining strawberries, make 4 rows to form stripes and the 50 blueberries to form starts.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Spread crushed graham crackers in the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour melted margarine over them.
Pat down with a large spoon.

title: make-ahead seven layer salad
directions: Dressing:
Combine mayonnaise, yogurt, parsley and cayenne pepper.

title: string beans au gratin
directions: Wash and boil cleaned string beans in a pot with about 4 quarts of water and salt for about 15 minutes until tender, but not completely done.
Drain in a colander.
Combine 1 ounce of butter and chopped onion in a pan.
Heat for about 2 minutes, without browning, then add beans, pepper and nutmeg.
Stir for 2 more minutes and pour in a buttered baking pan.
Beat eggs slightly and blend in cream and grated cheese.
Pour mixture over beans and bake until gratin is formed.
Serves 6 persons.

title: my favorite cheese cake
directions: Mix crackers, sugar and margarine together and press in the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Preheat oven to 300°.

title: seven-up sherbet punch
directions: Raspberry, pineapple, lemon, orange or cranberry sherbet can be used.
Try using one quart lemon sherbet with one quart of any other flavor.
Put the two quarts of sherbet in a punch bowl and let stand at room temperature.
Just before serving, when the sherbet is slightly mushy, add the chilled 7-Up and stir several times.
Makes 50 generous servings.

title: lemon supreme pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine first 6 ingredients and beat for 3 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan until cake tests done.
Cool for 15 minutes in pan before removing.
Combine confectioners sugar and lemon juice and glaze slowly while cake is still warm.

title: lemon bundt cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box of cake mix, using cake mix, eggs and oil. Then add lemon jello to mixture and stir in. Grease and flour Bundt pan and pour mixture into pan.
Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Before cake is done, mix powdered sugar and lemon juice with a fork. You may want to add more sugar or juice, it depends on how much and how thick you like your glaze.
Then pour over top of cake when you take cake out of oven and put on cake plate.

title: texas b.b.q. sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a sauce pan.
Simmer 15 minutes or until it thickens slightly.

title: homemade dog biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water (110° to 115°). Stir in broth and molasses.
Add 1 cup of the all-purpose flour, the whole wheat flour, cracked wheat, cornmeal, dry milk, garlic and 2 teaspoons of salt.
Mix well.
On floured surface, knead in remaining flour.
Roll out, half at a time, to 3/8-inch thickness. Cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheets. Brush tops with mixture of egg and milk.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Bake in a 300° oven for 45 minutes. Turn oven off.
Let dry overnight in oven.
Makes 42 to 48.

title: indian tiki bread
directions: Combine all ingredients well until it is to the consistency of hush puppies.
Pour oil in electric frypan and drop by tablespoon in oil.
Cook until done.

title: french toast
directions: Cook corn syrup, butter and brown sugar until it bubbles. Add pecans and pour mixture into a 9X13 inch pan.

Layer a loaf of french toast bread or texas toast bread on top of pecan mixture. Beat together eggs, milk, and vanilla and pour evenly over bread. Refrigerate overnight and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Flip over on large platter and serve warm with warm syrup, fresh strawberries, and cool whip.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Boil pasta.
Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream pound cake #7
directions: Cream
Crisco and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla;
add
milk
and
flour
gradually.
Stir in sour cream, but do not do any unnecessary mixing after adding sour cream. Bake in a 10-inch tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Chop cold meat very fine.
Season with pepper, nutmeg and onion.
Melt butter; add flour and mix until smooth.
Add cream and cook slowly, stirring constantly until sauce is thick.
Add chopped meat and salt.
Chill.
Shape into croquettes.
Dip into eggs, then into bread crumbs.
Roll lightly in shape.
Fry in hot fat until browned, about 5 minutes.

title: no fuss broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, corn and egg. Pour into square baking dish. Take melted margarine and put into the stuffing crumbs. Mix well. Spread over broccoli mixture. Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: lipton onion potatoes
directions: Melt butter and put in a Ziploc bag, along with the rest of the ingredients. Shake and after potatoes are evenly coated, place in shallow baking dish. Bake at 450° for 40 minutes.

title: chrusty (angel's wings)
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar until fluffy, and add vanilla.
Mix flour with baking powder.
Add sour cream, rum and beaten egg yolks.
Knead well.
Cut off a little part of the dough (cover the rest with plastic) and roll very thin.
Cut in 2 x 4-inch strips. Cut a hole in the middle of each strip, then pass one end of each strip through it to make a knot.
Fry until golden brown in hot Crisco shortening.
After cooling, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake, covered, 15 minutes in 425° oven; drain.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch and oregano. Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Pour heated sauce over chicken; top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes, uncovered. Garnish with parsley.

title: old time egg custard
directions: Beat egg yolks until blended.
Melt butter until just warm. Add sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Mix thoroughly at medium speed of electric mixer.
Gradually add milk.
Pour mixture into a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake in preheated 325° oven until filling is firm, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with meringue.
Place in oven until brown.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion in half of the margarine.
Add broccoli and simmer until tender.
Add remainder of ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Serve hot with Fritos or other chips.

title: quick poppy seed - lemon loaf
directions: In bowl stir together flour, baking powder, poppy seed, salt, and lemon peel.
Combine eggs, milk, oil, and honey.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Turn into two greased 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pans on rack for 10 minutes; remove from pans. Cut in slices and serve warm.

title: chicken with rice bake
directions: Place pieces of chicken in a large baking dish or pan.
Pour dry rice over chicken pieces.
Spoon the cream of chicken soup evenly over the chicken and rice.
Repeat with can of water. Cover and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese together.
Sprinkle in gelatin.
Add drained cherries and stir together.
Chill and serve.

title: spiced fruit
directions: Grate and peel orange, reserving grated rind. Cut orange into 4 or 5 slices. Combine with rind, pears, peaches and pineapple in a large bowl. Combine remaining ingredients in a 1-quart microwave casserole. Microwave at HIGH for 3 to 5 minutes. Pour over fruit; cover and chill several hours or overnight. Remove cinnamon and cloves before serving. Nice for breakfast or as a dessert. Yield: 4 servings or more.

title: cheesy party rye
directions: Toast 1 side of party rye slices.
Spread the above mixture on flipped side of rye slices.
Broil until cheese is bubbly.

title: brandy crush
directions: Boil water and sugar; turn off heat.
Add Five Alive juice and brandy.
Put in 3 or 4 small containers in freezer.
When ready to use, put in glass and add 7-Up.
Very good.

title: yeast waffles
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in salt and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients. This makes a thin batter and can be stored in the refrigerator up to 5 days.
Make the night before.

title: old fashion sauerkraut soup
directions: Cook some pork bones and reserve that meat.
Cook potatoes and add meat, sauerkraut and salt.
Cook for about 10 minutes and simmer for 2 hours.

title: hungarian baked chicken
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet. Dust chicken lightly with paprika. Brown chicken on all sides over medium heat.
Cook chicken 30 minutes.

title: marylou's special brunch
directions: *They will stick together, so separate and put in greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.

title: jeannie's meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef and Stove Top stuffing together.
Add tomato sauce and salt to taste.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Use part of flour to coat chopped fruit and nuts. Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well. Fold in remaining flour; add fruit and nuts. Bake in greased and floured cake pan at 250°, approximately 3 hours. Partly cool before removing from pan.

title: orange corn muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, combine egg, milk, oil and orange peel.
Add to cornmeal mixture, stirring just until ingredients are combined.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove from tins and serve warm.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together dry cake mix, 2 eggs and butter.
Spread in oblong cake pan (13 x 9-inch).
Sprinkle on coconut and pecans. In a bowl, mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour on top and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Use large pot.
Fill 1/2 full with water.
Put ground meat in water and start cooking.
Add all remaining items; bring to a boil.
Turn down heat.
Continue cooking real slow for approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken and dumplins
directions: Cook chicken in water and 1 teaspoon salt until tender. Debone chicken and set aside. Let broth cool (see below).

title: pizza sandwiches
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add oregano, salt, pepper, tomato paste and Parmesan cheese.
Cut loaf of French bread lengthwise.
Spread with butter.
Spread meat mixture on top of bread.
Add slices of cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until hot all the way through and cheese is melted.

title: grandma bartoletti's potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by the tablespoonful into a pan with melted shortening.
Cook until golden brown over medium to medium-high heat.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package.
Place ice cream cones in muffin tins.
Fill cones 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake according to box.
Let cool.
Frost.

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Mix crushed Oreos and margarine.
Spread 1/2 of the mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate while mixing other ingredients. Mix 1/2 of Cool Whip and 8 ounces cream cheese until blended well.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding with 2 1/2 cups cold milk. Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and sprinkle rest of Oreo mixture on top.
Refrigerate.

title: peas and asparagus
directions: Put peas and asparagus in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Drain.
Add oleo and simmer until oleo melts.
Add cheese and melt.
Mix and heat on low until mixture is heated through.
It's best if it doesn't boil.
Reheat leftovers in oven.
Delicious with roast.

title: tofu spinach quiche
directions: Stir together all except spinach.
Add spinach and pour into 8-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together (except nuts) well.
Shape into 2 balls and roll in chopped nuts.
Chill.

title: mom's sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Add eggs, singly, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda together.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with sour cream, blending after each addition.
Spread half of the batter in a 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and lined on the bottom.

title: orange slush
directions: Put both ingredients in blender; mix until smooth and thick. Divide between 2 (8 ounce) glasses.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Special Equipment:
Pastry bag with star tip.

title: fancy farm 24 hour picnic slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients; let set while preparing the dressing.

title: mother's best ever pie crust
directions: Cream the Crisco, milk and water until all liquid is gone. You can do this by hand or with electric mixer, but be careful not to spill liquid.

Add flour and salt, then mix well with hands. Divide into 2 equal pieces. This is a wetter dough than most people are used to, so I recommend using waxed paper to roll out dough, then transfer to pie pans, first removing top layer of waxed paper.
Flip dough so the sticky side will be resting in your palm.
Fit to your pie pan, then very gently remove remaining waxed paper.
Roll edges and crimp or press with fork tines. Makes enough for 1 double crust or 2 shells.

title: layered salad
directions: Dissolve cherry jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Pour into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 1/2-inch dish.
Chill until layer is firm.

title: shrimp stew "cajun style"
directions: Make roux by adding flour and oil until dark brown over slow fire.
Careful not to burn.
Saute vegetables in roux when brown. Cook about 10 to 15 minutes, then add shrimp.
Saute all together until pink or cooked.
Have some water boiling on stove where shrimp is cooked, then add water slowly to mixture until desired gravy thickness.
Add some Kitchen Bouquet if gravy is too light. Will darken it.
Cook covered on low, about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: mexican madness
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Mix soup, beans, sauce and tomatoes.
Place tortillas in a long shallow casserole dish.
Pour meat over tortillas.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dorothy burrows chocolate pie(microwave)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a microwave proof bowl.
Add milk slowly to mix.
Microwave for 3 minutes.
In the meantime, beat egg yolks. Remove milk mixture from microwave and add a little of the mixture to egg yolks.
Stir.
Add egg yolks to milk mixture, stir and return to microwave.
Microwave for 3 more minutes, stirring after each minute.
(May need to cook a little longer, depending on microwave).
Mixture should leave a ditch when spoon is pulled from one side of bowl to the other.
Add margarine and vanilla, pour into baked pie shell.
Prepare meringue from egg whites.
Put on cooled pie and brown under broiler.

title: art's mint brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, beat together the first 6 ingredients to make brownie layer.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until firm.
Cool.

title: tuna fish scallop
directions: Arrange tuna and egg slices in shallow baking dish, 6 x 8-inches.
Melt margarine; blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk slowly and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over tuna mixture; top with cheese and crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers.
Pour in casserole dish and top with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine with other ingredients. Pour into buttered casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add cabbage.
Peel and dice apples. Add salt and sugar.
Add 2 cups of water and 1 bay leaf.
Add vinegar; simmer 1 hour, covered.
Check for doneness.
Add more vinegar and salt for taste.

title: baked ricotta custard
directions: Preheat oven to 250° F.
Beat cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Add ricotta cheese; beat until well blended.
Gradually add Splenda No Calorie Sweetener, Granular, beating until blended.
Add eggs gradually, beating until blended.
Add egg white and beat until blended.
Add vanilla and half and half, beating until blended.
Pour mixture into 8 (8 ounce) ramekins; place ramekins in a roasting pan.
Add hot water to pan to a depth of 1 inch.
Bake at 250° F for 45 minutes or until custards are set.
Custards will puff slightly and remain white. Remove from water bath and cool on a wire rack.
Serve chilled or at room temperature.
Garnish, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately. Then add all other ingredients and mix with a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan.

title: mom's texas barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over low heat 30 to 45 minutes.

title: kids dog biscuits
directions: Mix water and oil.
Add flour.
Roll out.
Cut with cookie cutters and bake at 350° until brown.

title: christmas rice
directions: Combine rice, soup, water, pepper and onion in casserole dish. Mix well.
Add pimento and stir again.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together and spread in pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: tuna or chicken salad bake
directions: Saute in skillet until tender the diced celery and onions and margarine.
Mix in the rest of ingredients, except chip crumbs, and pour into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Then sprinkle crumbs over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush
Oreos
in
food processor.
Cream butter, cheese and sugar.
In	separate bowl mix pudding and milk until well blended. Then
blend
in Cool Whip.
Add this to cream cheese mixture. Layer in 8-inch flower pot, starting with cookie mix (dirt),
a few
gummy	worms
and
then
pudding/cream cheese mixture. Continue layers, ending with dirt.	Freeze for later use.
Take out
of
freezer
at
least 1 hour before serving. Decorate
with artificial flowers, etc. and serve with a small garden spade.

title: dream pie
directions: Take crusts and press pecans into bottom of crust. Bake and cool. Mix sugar and cream cheese. In another bowl, whip Dream Whip according to the directions on the box. Combine both mixtures and pour into pie crusts. Top with blueberry or strawberry pie filling and chill.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cup sugar, water and salt until sugar dissolves. Place on top of stove on high heat.

title: hot chili
directions: Brown meat in large pan.
Stir in onion and celery.
Stir in tomatoes (cut up and drained).
Add salt, pepper, chili powder and garlic powder.
Add beans.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: quick nacho dip
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat; drain.
Add beans, picante sauce and taco seasoning mix, stirring well.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.

title: salmon burgers or loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Can form cakes and fry or put in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: Saute ham in 3 tablespoons fat in saucepan or pot.
Add onions and garlic.
Stir in water, herbs, salt, pepper, Tabasco sauce and peas.
Bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and boil gently for 1 hour.
Stir often.

title: honey turkey loaf
directions: Mix together and make into loaf and drizzle honey on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Slice and serve.
Serves 8.

title: granola
directions: Mix all ingredients except fruits together with hands and get all lumps out of brown sugar.
Bake in roasting pan at 325° until golden brown, about 45 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add raisins, chopped figs or other dried fruits, if desired.
Keep in plastic bags or cannister in refrigerator or freezer.

title: chicken 'n cabbage casserole
directions: In plastic bag, mix flour, seasoned salt and celery seed.
Add chicken a few pieces at a time, shaking to coat.
Heat oil to medium temperature.
Add chicken and fry until brown.
Remove and place in a shallow baking dish.
Cook onion in the frying pan for 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, sauce, caraway seed, salt and sugar and heat to boiling.
Add cabbage and stir.
Spoon cabbage mixture over chicken.
Place some under chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Remove foil and sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: sarah's peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: In left hand, hold one slice of bread.
Cover liberally with peanut butter.
Cover other slice with jelly.
Slap the slices together and cut in half diagonally.
Serve with chocolate milk.

title: pear chutney
directions: Put all together in a large pan. Bring to a boil.
Let bubble 20 or 25 minutes. Test to see if pears are done.
Put in jars. Makes 13 pints.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed and drain.
Brown beef.
Stir in cheese.
Brown onion and pepper.
Mix all ingredients with the macaroni.
Stir in Ragu sauce.
Top with macaroni and cheese. Bake until done.

title: triple broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Slightly thaw broccoli.
Break apart; set broccoli aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add broccoli; stir to mix well.
Pour into shallow ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until golden (light) brown.

title: chilli
directions: Cover ground beef and onions with water.
Cook 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Boil for 15 minutes.

title: easy pecan pies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a 9-inch pie shell in a 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the cranberries and sugar and let sit 15 minutes.
Mix jello as directed.
Add chopped ingredients.
Pour into mold or shallow dish.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix sugars, eggs, margarine and soda. Add vanilla, peanut butter, oatmeal, chocolate chips and M&M's. Chill dough. Roll into walnut-size balls. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: paczki (pronounced "punck-key")
directions: Beat egg
yolks, well.	Add sugar, melt together, stick of butter and	milk until warm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add this mixture to
yolks and sugar.
Add salt, lemon rind or vanilla, gradually; add
some
of the flour; add 3 tablespoons melted butter and rest of the flour.
Beat well until dough no longer clings to
spoon.
Set
aside.
Let	rise
for
about 2 hours.
Take small piece
of
dough
and flatten it out in the palm of your hand.	Put
about a teaspoonful of jam in center, fold edges of dough
to
form
a
ball.
Fry ball in deep fat, heated to 350°
for about 5 minutes.
When done, sprinkle with 10x sugar or frost
with
an
icing
of
sugar and butter combined.

title: fawn pie
directions: Mix together and pour into 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hobo ham salad
directions: Grind the bologna.
Mix all 3 ingredients together.
Make sandwiches.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix hamburger, pork, rice, onion, mushrooms with liquid, salt, pepper, garlic salt and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Core cabbage and place in large pot of boiling water.
Remove cabbage leaves from head.
Drain leaves.
Place 1/3 cup on each leaf.
Roll, then push end in toward the center.
Place seam side down on baking dish. Mix remaining tomato sauce, sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour.
If you want sauce thicker, mix cornstarch and 1 tablespoon water in saucepan. Stir in liquid from cabbage rolls.
Heat to a boil.
Serve with cabbage rolls.

title: dairy queen ice cream
directions: Heat milk to almost scalding.
Put gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water, then pour into hot milk.
Also add sugar, salt, marshmallows and corn syrup.
Cover and let set a little until things are dissolved, then add vanilla.
Pour into freezer can and let set in cold place until firm before freezing.
Pour can of Milnot on top.

title: dilled seafood mousse
directions: In a saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over 1 cup broth.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Heat until mixture boils and gelatin is completely dissolved.
Pour into large bowl.
Add all other ingredients except Cool Whip and mix well.
Chill in freezer 10 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into 8 cup ring mold; chill 3 hours or overnight. Unmold on serving plate; garnish with dill sprigs.
Makes 16 servings.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a saucepan; add pineapple and cherries, cooking until thickened.
Take off heat; add dried jello.
Let cool; add bananas and nuts.
Pour in 2 graham cracker crusts. Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and refrigerate.
In separate bowl, mix cut up broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon. Combine ingredients from both bowls and chill.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: Coat a large Dutch oven with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add turkey, onion and garlic; cook until turkey is browned, stirring until it crumbles.
Drain turkey mixture.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Wipe skillet with paper towel.
Drain spinach and press dry between layers of paper towels.
Return turkey mixture to skillet.
Add spinach, tomato and next 7 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes or until thick, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Combine Ricotta cheese and egg substitute in a small bowl; stir well.

title: homemade rolls
directions: In one bowl, mix lukewarm water and yeast (mix well).
In another bowl, mix sugar, butter, egg and salt.
Combine all ingredients except flour.
Mix well.
Gradually add plain flour. Store in a greased container; cover and refrigerate.
As needed, roll out, let rise and bake.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray baking dish (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch) with nonstick cooking spray.
Place cilantro sprigs, parsley sprigs, salsa, lime juice and garlic in blender or food processor. Blend for 30 seconds or until smooth.
Reserve half of mixture. Mix remaining salsa mixture, the chicken and 1/4 cup of cheese. Spoon about 1/4 cup chicken mixture in each tortilla.
Roll up tortilla and place, seam side down, in baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Simmer all ingredients, except crushed tomatoes and wine. When lightly browned, add canned crushed tomatoes and cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Last 15 minutes, add wine.
Can be used over cooked spaghetti or rice.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Mix 1/2 cup tomato sauce, ketchup, water, and sugar and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Cut peppers in half.
Spoon mixture into peppers.
Pour sauce over peppers.
Put in microwave-safe dish.
Cover it.
Cook on Medium-high (75%) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6 people.

title: frank's favorite fudge brownies
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar.
Blend in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla. Stir in flour and nuts; mix well.
Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Cool.
Cut into 16 squares.

title: beef tips and gravy(crock-pot)
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot; stir and cover.
Cook approximately 6 to 8 hours on low heat.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: caramel icing
directions: Put in saucepan.
Cook at moderate heat until a soft ball stage is reached using a candy thermometer.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix.
Allow to cool and ice.

title: fudge candy
directions: Put sugar, cocoa and butter together in a pot.
Add milk.
Put on a hot burner and stir constantly.
Let come to rolling boil and begin to time for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from burner and add vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to drop on wax paper or buttered dish.
Work fast because it sets up quickly.
You can add nuts, if desired.

title: tuna balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except corn flakes.
Form into balls. Roll in corn flakes and fry in hot fat until brown.
Makes 75 balls.
Serve with hot cocktail sauce made with ketchup and prepared horseradish to taste.

title: roman apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs and milk until blended.
Add chopped apples to mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish.

title: crab ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, crabmeat, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well and form into ball.
Refrigerate.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Blend all together except chips.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add chips and pour into greased tube pan.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans.
Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cream shortening and sugar until light; add vanilla. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to creamed shortening mixture alternately with sour cream.
Place half of batter in pan.
Combine softened butter with the brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle the batter with about 1/2 this mixture.
Add remaining batter and top with rest of brown sugar mixture.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes before removing it.

title: very moist cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Frost.
You can experiment with flavors:
orange cake with orange frosting or yellow cake with strawberry frosting.

title: mom's banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Fold in Eagle Brand and Cool Whip.
Line bottom of dish with vanilla wafers.
Repeat layers of sliced bananas and pudding mixture.
Top with vanilla crumbs.

title: old fashion pot pie
directions: Cook ham with bone in water in 6 qt. pot.
Chicken or beef with bone may also be used.
When meat is tender, remove meat from bone and return to broth.
Keep pot about 3/4 full with water.
Put all dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Add crisco, working together with hands until fine and mixed well.
Combine broth with cold water until lukewarm or 1 cup.
Start adding cooled broth in small amounts until dough forms a firm dough or ball.
Roll dough about 1/4 inch thick.
Cut in strips about 1 1/2 inches wide and 2 inches long.
Be sure water is boiling before adding dough.
Put in 6 to 8 pieces of dough at a time then punch down with fork under water; it will double in size.
Keep adding dough until gone.
Dice potatoes and put in pot.
Cook over medium heat for about 20 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Stir often.

title: chocolate-mint refresher
directions: Crush candies in blender.
Add cocoa and sugar; blend well. Add milk and ice cream.
Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately. Garnish with mint leaves, if desired.

title: great popovers
directions: Break eggs into mixer bowl; beat until frothy.
Beat in milk and butter.
Slowly beat in flour and salt.
Batter should be light but not foamy (if batter becomes lumpy, strain it).
Popover batter may be prepared ahead and stored in covered pitcher.
Stir before pouring into custard cups.
If popovers are to be baked immediately, preheat oven to 400°.
Generously oil custard cups, filling each to within 1/2-inch of the top.
Arrange cups on a cookie sheet for easier handling.
Place in preheated oven.
Bake until very dark brown and well done (about 1 hour for 6-ounce cups, 45 minutes for 4-ounce cups).

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter
and sugars.
Blend in egg, peanut butter, salt and
vanilla.
Stir
in
flour
and
oats.
Spread
into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle
with chocolate chips.
Return to oven and let chips melt,
then
spread as a frosting.
Cool and cut into 1 1/2 x 2-inch fingers.

title: classic sour cream cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Beat in eggs, then sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly brown around edge. Cool, then chill.
Top with cherry filling and refrigerate.

title: flavored frostings
directions: Whip ingredients to a fluffy texture.
Add any flavored Kool-Aid to frosting and whip more.
Frosting will have the Kool-Aid flavor.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine, then add egg.
Mix, then add all other ingredients.
Form into small balls and flatten with a flat bottom glass that has been dipped in melted margarine, then sugar, then press the cookie dough.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix wafer crumbs with 1 stick melted butter; spread on bottom of long Pyrex dish.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs and 2 sticks butter in mixer for 15 minutes.
Then spread onto wafer crumbs; then chill.
After it has been chilled, slice bananas on this.
Then pour drained pineapple over this and spread Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.

title: raspberry champagne punch
directions: In blender container, puree raspberries.
In punch bowl, combine pureed raspberries, lemon juice, sugar and wine.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, scoop sherbet into punch bowl.
Add champagne slowly.
Stir gently.
Yield:
3 quarts.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; drain grease.
Add chili with beans; heat and mix well.
Cool.
Then in a big bowl, mix shredded lettuce, onion, pepper, tomatoes and cheese.
Add salt and pepper. When ready to serve, add meat mixture to lettuce mixture.
Toss in crushed Doritos.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Brown in a heavy skillet the ground beef, garlic button and chopped onion.
Add cloves, chili powder, Tabasco sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Then add catsup or chili sauce, prepared mustard, cream of chicken soup and water.
Simmer in the heavy skillet.
The longer the better.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Drain olives.
Slice cheese into 1/4-inch slices.
Wrap olive in cheese; roll into ball with palm of hands.
Roll balls in finely chopped pecans.
Chill; slice balls in half shortly before serving.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Separately, beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla to eggs.
Beat.
Add the scalded milk to the egg and vanilla mixture.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with some of the butter.
Place bread and raisins in the pan.
Then pour the warm milk mixture over the bread.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until a knife comes out clean.
At 30 minutes into cooking time, stir the mixture lightly, otherwise the bread will sink to the bottom.

title: apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin tins (1/2 cup muffin tins).
Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt into a medium bowl.

title: oriental oven barbecue
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Place chicken on rack in foil-lined roasting pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Combine ketchup, hoisin sauce, soy sauce and brown sugar.
Mix well; brush generously over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes longer, brushing with sauce occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: banana muffins
directions: Put together flour, sugar, soda, nutmeg and salt.
Beat egg in bowl, add butter and vanilla.
Add mashed bananas.
Beat well. Stir flour and sugar mixture in with the rest.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot dip
directions: Mix and keep in fridge.
Serve only on Chicken in a Biskit crackers.
Great for parties.

title: trash apples
directions: In saucepan add apples, sugar, water and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until apples are tender.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli spears first; barely cover with water in a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole per package directions.
Add and mix all other ingredients.
Do not drain water from broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low-fat, low sodium salad dressing
directions: Fix stuffing.
Taking each slice of beef, layer with stuffing and roll up.
Place rolled up beef into shallow pan; cover with gravy and bake in oven or microwave until hot.
Cook broccoli; drain.
Stir in cheese soup.
Makes a delicious, quick and easy company dinner.

title: chocolate mint cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients for 4 minutes.
Add green food color. Fold in mini chips.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, tomato paste and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Press crescent rolls in 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle 1/8 cup Parmesan cheese over crust. Spoon half of meat mixture onto crust.
Put 2 slices Mozzarella cheese over meat mixture.
Put rest of meat and Parmesan cheese in pie pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Put 2 slices of Mozzarella cheese on top of pie in crisscross fashion.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: squash haters zucchini
directions: Peel zucchini; remove seeds.
Shred; add to salt and boiling water.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring often.
Do not overcook.
Drain; reserve 1/3 cup liquid.
Remove from pan.
Saute bacon until crisp; remove from pan and saute onion in the bacon fat until golden and soft.
Do not brown.
Add flour; stir.
Add reserved squash liquid and bring to a boil.
Add sour cream; combine squash and sauce.
Sprinkle bacon over top of squash just before serving.

title: "peg's" pea salad
directions: Mix lettuce, celery, cooked peas, green peppers and onion in large bowl.
In a small bowl, mix the sour cream, sugar and mayonnaise together.
Add to lettuce mixture and mix well. Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top.

title: sugar crusted apples
directions: Core and peel apples.
In small bowl, mix sugar, flour and cinnamon with blender.
Cut in butter with flour until mixture is crumbly.
In cup beat egg and brush over apples.
Coat with sugar flour mixture.
Bake in shallow dish.
Pour cider in bottom of dish.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage over medium heat until done, stirring to crumble well; drain sausage on paper towels and set aside.
Spread each slice of bread with butter; cut into cubes.
Place bread cubes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; sprinkle with sausage and top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat well and pour over mixture in baking pan.
Chill at least 8 hours; remove from refrigerator.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
If put into glass baking dish, check at 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook chopped broccoli and drain.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add soup and water.
Add cheese and seasonings. Stir until cheese melts.
Add broccoli.
Stir in rice.
Pour into casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups of boiling water. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Stir in 1/2 stick of the butter; set aside. Beat eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla and rest of butter and add to rice; mix well. Add raisins, if desired. Pour into 2-quart casserole dish. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until lightly browned. Delicious served either hot or cold. Makes 8 servings. Preparation time: 1:00

title: danish puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure first cup of flour into bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons water and mix with fork.
Form into ball and divide in half.
Pat with hands into 2 large strips (3 x 12-inches).
Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Mix 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup water in small saucepan and bring to rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add extract.
Stir in flour, all at once.
When smooth and thick, add one egg at a time, beating smoothly.
Divide and spread half evenly over each piece of pastry.
Bake 60 minutes.
Frost at once with confectioners sugar icing and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash banana.
Add sugars, oil, milk and egg; mix well.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to mixture; mix well. Stir in nuts.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes in greased cake tin.

title: sandy's hamburger green bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in large skillet.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix hamburger with tomato soup.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Place green beans on top.
Prepare instant mashed potatoes according to package directions for 4 to 6 servings. Spread over green beans.
Top with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and slightly brown.
A meal-in-one!
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple-lime fluff
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Cool Whip thoroughly.
Stir in dry Jell-O.
Fold in pineapple.
Chill.

title: cloud cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in cereal; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes, or until golden brown.
Let cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: classic butter cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually beat in sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and almond extract.
Gradually blend in flour.
Chill dough for ease in handling.
Roll dough out to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut in to desired shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 8 to 12 minutes until golden.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Decorate as desired.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish.
Sprinkle rice over.
Combine soup and water and pour over rice.
Season with salt and pepper. Dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle soup mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup of rice over that.
Place chicken over the rice.
Mix soup and water. Pour over all.
Cover with foil and cook in 350° oven for 1 hour. Freezes well.

title: ude rice(excellent with marinated flank steak)
directions: Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cover when liquids are absorbed.

title: pain perdu-french toast(creole cooking)
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and cinnamon. Dip bread into mixture. Fry in hot deep fat in skillet on each side
until edges begin to brown.
Remove and drain.
Serve hot with bacon, ham or sausage, if desired.

title: watergate cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine cake mix, pudding and Crisco oil. Add 7-Up, eggs and pecans.
Blend well.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream cheese and butter. Add water. Add dry ingredients sifted together. Let stand in fridge for 2 hours. Roll out thin, cut and bake at 450 for 10-12 minutes.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck with diced onion.
Drain grease from meat and add mushrooms; cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce, tomato soup, water, oregano, salt and pepper; simmer.
Cook spaghetti with water, garlic oil and salt; drain.
Serve with meat sauce.

title: okra with tomato sauce
directions: Boil the meat with 3 cups water, whole onion, black pepper, cinnamon, 1 tsp. salt, and cardamom, about 45-60 minutes or until meat is cooked.
After the meat is done cooking, it must have 2-3 cups of water remaining in it.
Pour 2 Tbsp. of the oil in a pot and fry okras on medium heat for 10 minutes.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Melt
butter;
add
sugar
and cocoa and mix well.
Add milk and vanilla. Cook to rolling boil and boil for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Add oats and chopped pecans.
Spoon out on wax paper while hot.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups of flour, yeast, salt, sugar and baking soda in a large bowl.
Heat milk until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add milk to dry mixture; beat well.
Stir in enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into well-greased and corn meal dusted pans. Sprinkle tops with corn meal.
Cover and let rise for 45 minutes. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans at once.
Cool on racks.
Slice; toast and enjoy!

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add buttermilk, then vanilla.
Add soda, baking powder and flour.
Mix well with electric beaters.
When well mixed, add oil.
Keeps overnight.
Have hot waffles for breakfast.

title: my favorite plain cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour mix into tube pan and bake for 45 minutes.
Delicious!

title: baked mac and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Heat milk, soup and butter in small casserole dish; layer macaroni, cheese and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken gumbo soup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer about 1 hour.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoons.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fried garden gumbo
directions: Mix all ingredients together and coat with flour and corn meal. Fry in skillet of oil until tender and golden brown.

title: smothered pork roast
directions: Season roast with salt, pepper, and seasoning salt.
Add fresh mushroom and onion.
Cook
in crockpot or oven until done. Add soup with broth to make nice gravy.
Pour over roast and let simmer for 15 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until crumbly. Add yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Mix well.

title: curried rice and chicken
directions: Take 1 salt cured ham.
Soak overnight or 24 hours in water; pour water out.
Wash and trim ham.
Place ham in lard can with a lid on bottom of can so ham won't stick.
Cover with water. Gradually raise temperature on burner for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Bring to hard boil 1 1/2 hours.
Take off; place in tub or large container on quilts.
Cover tightly, using newspaper between tub and quilts.
Pile a lot of quilts on top or whatever you have, so heat will not escape.
Let sleep 24 hours.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 5 minutes.
Beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir in all dry ingredients.
Spread on greased and floured pan (15 x 10 x 1).
Bake on 375° for 15 minutes.
When finished baking, flip over onto a kitchen towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up in towel and let cool.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add egg yolks, butter, vanilla and milk.
Mix and pour into pie shell; bake until done.
Beat egg whites for meringue.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Process until smooth.
Makes enough for 2 heads of romaine lettuce.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Flatten out crescent dough.
Spread with sausage and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Roll up and wrap in foil or plastic wrap. Chill until very firm but not frozen (in freezer).
Slice 1/4-inch thick and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together sugar
and
butter.
Add flour and eggs; beat well.
Add	buttermilk,
vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake
at 350° in preheated oven for 45 to 50 minutes. Makes 3 pies.

title: vegetable omelet
directions: Chop up onion, mushrooms, pepper and celery.
Heat the oil in a frying pan until it gets hot.
Place the onion in the pan and cook until they turn brown, then place the remaining vegetables in the pan.
Next, beat up the eggs and mix them with the vegetables.
Add some salt and pepper for seasoning.
Fry the contents on a low flame.

title: glazed fruit
directions: Mix all together and bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.
This recipe keeps well in the refrigerator or if you prefer, divide the recipe and freeze 1/2 for later use.

title: rosie's cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Place in casserole dish. Spread mushroom soup over potatoes.
Cover with slices of Velveeta cheese. Place pats of butter on each cheese slice.
Pour milk over cheese.
Sprinkle top with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill dough, then form into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in powdered sugar (heavy).
Flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix ingredients with hands and form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy to make dinner rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; drop into greased muffin pan. Cook at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a heavy pan; bring to a boil. Cook beef until crumbled and brown.
Stir into vegetable mixture and add bouillon.
Reduce heat and simmer at least 20 minutes or longer.
Yields 2 quarts.
May be frozen.
Better the next day.

title: under the sea salad
directions: Mix lime jello with water and crushed pineapple and pour into mold.
Let set until stiff.
Combine lemon jello, water and let stand until syrupy.
Beat with beater.
Mix 1 pkg. cream cheese (6 oz.) and 1/2 c. whipping cream.
Whip together until thick and fold into lemon jello.
Pour over lime jello and let set.

title: a-1 strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, oleo and walnuts; spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; let cool.
Fold in whipped topping with 1 cup sugar and cream cheese. Put on top of first layer.
Spread strawberries on top.
Mix cornstarch, jello and water.
Put into 2-quart saucepan.
Cook until clear; cool and spread over strawberries.
Let set overnight.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix well and chill, then form into ball.
Roll in parsley.

title: mom's good potato salad
directions: Hard boil eggs and chop.
Dice potatoes into medium squares. Add all ingredients except paprika and fold carefully together.

title: barbecue chicken pizza
directions: Place pizza crust on ungreased cookie sheet.
Toss chicken with barbecue sauce; place evenly on crust.
Top with peppers, onion and cheese.
Bake at 450 degrees on bottom oven rack for 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese is melted and pizza crust is golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: gyoza (pot stickers)
directions: Mix all ingredients (except wrappers) by hand in a ball until mixed very well.
Spread wrappers on clean surface; divide filling evenly onto wrappers.
Wet edge of each wrapper with a little water and fold wrapper with filling in half.
Gather one edge of wrapper if you wish.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix well the butter, flour, sugar and milk; pour into baking dish.
Spoon the fruit; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: play dough(this is for "grandmas")
directions: Combine oil, Kool-Aid, alum and boiling water together.
Add salt and flour.
If too sticky, add more flour.
Put in airtight container.
Great fun for the grandkids!

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Heat milk and shortening until shortening melts.
Mix all together; pour in oiled small pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: d'ak-dori-tang(korean stewed chicken and potatoes)
directions: In a heavy pot, combine the chicken, potatoes, onion, red pepper flakes, garlic, sugar, soy sauce, rice wine, and sesame oil.
Mix together, then add 1/2 cup of water and mix again.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes over a medium flame. Add the green onions and cook for 3 more minutes.
Serve hot. Serves 2-3 people.

title: yogurt smoothies
directions: Blend all 5 ingredients together until smooth.
Makes 4 (7-ounce) drinks.

title: baked corn
directions: Add all ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve as vegetables.

title: caramel frosting and zucchini bars
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Cream together next 5 ingredients.
Combine both mixtures.
Gradually add zucchini, walnuts and butterscotch chips.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: In a medium sized saucepan, combine margarine or butter, sugar and dates.
Cook over medium-high heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add pecans and rice cereal. Form into small balls.
Roll balls in confectioners sugar. Yields about 8 dozen small balls.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet on top of stove and drain grease. Place all ingredients in casserole dish, stirring well, and add ground beef.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken tender casserole
directions: Line bottom of baking pan with bacon.
Put dry rice on top. Lay chicken on top; mix together water and soup and pour on top. Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: pickled roasted green peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake peppers for 15 to 20 minutes until the skins puff and blister.
Place in paper bag; close tightly and let stand 15 minutes.
Remove seeds and stems; cut into strips. Mix well with all remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: slow cook beef
directions: Place ingredients in slow cooker (crock-pot) for 10 to 12 hours on low heat.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Add sour cream if desired.

title: barney's chicken and yellow rice
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Bring 2 1/2 cups of broth to a boil. Pour in rice.
Chop veggies and saute.
Add veggies and deboned chicken to rice.
Season to taste.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Whip all ingredients, except marshmallows, until smooth.
Cook at 375° about 30 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and brown them.

title: almond punch
directions: Add
water as directed on each can.
Mix
all
ingredients. Put in containers and chill.
Chill punch bowl with ice cubes. Discard and add chilled punch.
Serve.

title: waldorf astoria red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make paste of coloring and cocoa and add to mixture.
Add buttermilk with salt alternately with flour and vanilla.
Lastly, add soda and vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in three 9 inch pans, greased and lined with wax paper.
Cool and cut in two crosswise sections and frost with the icing recipe.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, soda, cloves and cinnamon. Add shortening, brown sugar and buttermilk. Mix until all ingredients are moist. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Add eggs and beat 2 minutes more. Add jam and beat until well mixed. Bake in 2 greased and lightly floured 9-inch pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Frost with caramel glaze or butter cream.

title: hershey's light chocolate brownies
directions: *Two slightly beaten egg whites may be substituted.

title: souper eggs
directions: Season eggs with salt and pepper.
Blend eggs and soup.
Cook in omelet fashion; sprinkle with green pepper and onion.
When done, sprinkle crumbled bacon and chopped tomato.
Serve immediately.

title: redeemer bread(yes, church of the redeemer - houston)
directions: Mix oil, sugar, salt and bran cereal in a large mixing bowl. Pour boiling water over mixture and let cool.
Soften yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water. When bran mixture has cooled to lukewarm, add eggs, softened yeast and flour.
Mix thoroughly. Turn out on floured board.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes, drawing in more flour as needed to keep from being sticky.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double (1 1/4 hours).
Punch down.
Knead 2 minutes and shape into loaves or rolls.
(Makes 3 loaves.)
Let rise in greased pans until double (45 minutes). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes for loaves, 12 to 15 minutes for rolls.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar together and pour over mixed broccoli, bacon and onion.
Marinate overnight.

title: egg substitute
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender or food processor.
Blend for 30 seconds.

title: deviled crab
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion and celery in oleo, then mix with the rest of the ingredients.
If mixture is a little dry, add milk or water to desired consistency and fill shells.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, until brown.

title: fried rabbit
directions: Clean rabbit and cut into serving pieces.
Roll in flour, then salt and pepper.
Fry in oil until tender.
Do as you would if frying chicken.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix berries and sugar; let stand several hours or overnight. Add boiling water to lemon jello; stir to dissolve and add orange juice and other ingredients.
Pour into mold and cool until set.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Sprinkle the pork chops with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour; fry until lightly browned.
Place in casserole.
Cut over this mixture 1 medium onion (chopped), small bell pepper (chopped), 1/2 cup rice (more if desired), 1 can tomatoes (mashed) and 1 cup water.
Sprinkle with the 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper. Bake in a 450° oven for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole(a great tasting lunch without meat.)
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Cook onions and garlic until glazed.
Add eggplant, zucchini, bell peppers and spices.
Cook until eggplant is almost done.
Add tomatoes and cook 15 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and let cheese melt, or put in casserole dish, cover with cheese and bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sizzlin' tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toss together crumbs, cheese, butter and mustard.
Turn tomatoes, stem end down, and cut tomatoes into 5 slices, cutting to (but not through) the base.
Spread apart slightly and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spoon 2 tablespoons crumb mixture between each slice.

title: linza cookies(old european holiday cookie)
directions: In a very large bowl, mix flour and sugar together.
Make a well in the flour-sugar mixture and add butter, egg yolks and lemon rind.
Mix all together with your hands until thoroughly mixed like dough.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Place in a casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Stir by hand.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Skin chicken.
Arrange in skillet.
Pour Coca-Cola and barbecue sauce over chicken.
Let come to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: pickle rolls
directions: Warm cream cheese to about room temperature or until smooth. Spread cream cheese over 2 slices of corned beef; roll around pickle.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices. Serve chilled.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients with mixer.
Add the apples, coconut and chopped pecans.

title: cajun cake(chocolate sheet cake)
directions: Bring to a boil oleo, water and cocoa. Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt. Add to cocoa mixture and stir well. Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Mix well. Bake in 13 X 9 inch pan at 325 degrees for 25 minutes or until done. Frosting-melt and eat.

title: k-runch
directions: Melt Karo, sugar and peanut butter.
Mix in Special K cereal. Spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt both kinds of chips.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Chill and slice.

title: pan dressing
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Mix dressing; it will be juicy.
Use broth from bouillon.
Stew chicken and pick off bones; put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with cream of chicken soup.
Top with dressing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: milwaukee treats
directions: Saute meats until browned.
Drain excess fat.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Spread on rye bread.
Place on cookie sheet.
(May be frozen at this time and packaged for further use.)
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mom's sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all together and bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done. (She sometimes adds coconut, about 1/2 cup.)

title: dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add the blended eggs and milk.
Drop by teaspoon into boiling chicken broth, on stew or on top of boiling sauerkraut. Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Cover and cook for another 10 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese casserole
directions: Brown sausage, crumble it and drain away fat; set aside.
Boil noodles and drain.
In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter. Add flour until pasty.
Gradually pour in milk and stir until somewhat thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream, salt, pepper, parsley, egg, Parmesan cheese and blend together.
Mix with noodles.

title: fluffy chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix with 1 cup of the milk as directed on package in small mixer bowl.
Measure 2 cups of the prepared whipped topping and set aside.

title: chinese gravy
directions: Mix
cornstarch with water.
Add to rest of ingredients and cook until thick and clear.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Stir in taco seasoning mix and mix well.
Cool.
Tear lettuce in bite size pieces.
Add cooled meat.
Dice tomato and add to lettuce.
When ready to serve, add salad dressing, cheese and Doritos.
Do not add too early or Doritos will get soggy!

title: decorator frosting
directions: Mix ingredients together. Frost cooled cake.

title: baked beans
directions: In 2 1/2-quart casserole, combine beans, beef and onions. Stir in brown sugar, syrup, salt and pepper.
Cover and bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix well and beat 3 to 4 minutes.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Grease and flour pan lightly.

title: cole farms dressing
directions: Mix and stir in 1/2 cup sugar.

title: corn meal gravy
directions: Fry fatback; remove from skillet.
Add corn meal to grease and brown.
Add milk; stir until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Gravy will thicken in bowl.
Serve over toast.

title: mother's sweet potato stir-up
directions: Peel sweet potatoes and grate into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix milk, sugar and vanilla.
Taste to see if sweet enough. Pour slowly over the top of grated potatoes until you have them all covered.
(If you need more, add milk.)
Cut up butter into pads and put on top of the potatoes.
Cook for 1 hour in 400° oven. Good warm or cold.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix jello with water.
Add strawberries (juice included), pineapple (juice included) and bananas.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into long Pyrex dish.
Put in refrigerator until congealed.
When completely congealed, spread sour cream over top and add rest of Jell-O mixture.
Put back in refrigerator and congeal.

title: grilled tuna with papaya sauce
directions: One hour before serving, toss together ingredients. Keep at room
temperature. Grill meat until done. Top with sauce and serve.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and apple pie filling in large bowl.
Mix with wooden spoon.
Do not use mixer.
Hand mix.
Put in microwave cake pan and cook for 10 to 12 minutes on full power.
Check after 6 minutes and turn 1/2 turn.
Let cake cool.
Take frosting; heat in microwave for 10 seconds.
Stir and pour over cake to frost.

title: ranch bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix in other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato patties
directions: Mix the potatoes with the egg, onion and season with salt and pepper. Form your mix into 6 patties and cover in flour.
Brown in a moderately heated, oiled frying pan for about 5 minutes on each side.
Great substitute for mashed potatoes.

title: spanish pisto(eggplant)
directions: Heat oil in large frying pan.
Add onions, ham and garlic; saute.
Add peppers and eggplant; cook with vegetables in pan.
Add tomato and artichoke hearts; cook until eggplant is tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Don't overcook.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Blend first three ingredients.
Add cocoa.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add soda, salt and vanilla.
Alternate flour and buttermilk, starting with flour.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add all other ingredients except noodles and cheese.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole; put in a layer of noodles, a layer of Mozzarella cheese, a layer of Ricotta cheese and a layer of meat sauce. Repeat.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: lobster (langostino) rolls
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Flatten bread with rolling pin.

title: delicious cucumber soup(hot or cold)
directions: Put
all
ingredients in blender; blend well.
Then put in pan and bring to a slow boil.	Stir often.
Turn off heat. Stir again.
Let cool.
Serve very cold or serve hot.

title: orange cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place in refrigerator.

title: sparkling raspberry salad
directions: Drain package of frozen raspberries, reserving syrup. Dissolve package of raspberry gelatin in 2 cups boiling water. Add raspberry sherbet by spoonfuls, stirring until dissolved. Stir in frozen pink lemonade concentrate and the thawed raspberry syrup.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in raspberries and chopped nuts.

title: honey basil chicken
directions: In shallow baking dish, combine all ingredients except chicken.
Add chicken to marinade, turn to coat and refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Drain marinade from chicken and reserve. Transfer chicken to broiler.
Broil until no longer pink inside. Place reserved marinade in a 1-quart saucepan.
Simmer for 5 minutes or until reduced by half.
To serve, pour marinade over chicken.
Serves 4.

title: mom's foundation sugar cookies
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Gradually mix in dry ingredients. Roll dough to about 1/4-inch thick and cut cookie shapes.
May be easier to do on lightly floured surface or tea towel.

title: no bake cherry pie(child's recipe)
directions: Fill pie crust with filling. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with Oreo bits.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg.
Press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and eggs until smooth.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: reeses peanut butter cup
directions: Combine brown sugar and powdered sugar, peanut butter, and 1 stick butter. Mix well.
Pat out in a large greased glass pan. Melt chocolate chips and 2 Tbsp. butter.
Spread over peanut butter.
Let cool and cut in small squares.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put all
of the first 6 ingredients in a greased baking dish. Mix the
last
two	ingredients and put on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beer batter onion rings
directions: In warm bowl, dissolve 2 packages yeast in 1 cup warm beer. Add flour and salt and stir.
Add more beer (about 1 cup) as needed for "sticky run" dough.
Cover with cloth and let stand in warm place for 1/2 hour.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Batter onion rings and fry in hot oil.

title: sausage toast hors d'oeuvre
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Cut Velveeta into small pieces and add to warm sausage to allow to melt.
(Microwave if needed.)
Put mixture on bread.
Warm in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until cheese melts.
Serve hot.
A great recipe to make ahead and freeze.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Soften butter, cream butter and sugar until fluffy, add sour cream and egg yolks one at a time beating well after each.
Add flour gradually, vanilla, lemon juice.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour in greased bundt pan and put in cold oven.
Cook 325 for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add pineapple, strawberries and bananas.
Cover and chill.
Then spread sour cream.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper, mustard and butter.
Beat eggs and cream.
Add slowly, beating constantly, bringing all back to boil, then remove from heat and cool.
Keep in jar in refrigerator.
Add mayonnaise as needed when used.

title: strawberry yogurt dip
directions: I have no time to be

title: stir-drop sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in oil, vanilla and lemon juice.
Blend in sugar.
Add flour and baking powder.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with greased bottom of a drinking glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: kim's great beefsteak
directions: Optional:
You may add mushrooms, carrots, potatoes, etc.

title: grit casserole
directions: Cook grits by directions on box using 3 1/2 cups water.
Add cheese, oleo, milk and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in uncovered baking dish until firm.
May sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: caramels
directions: Melt butter in pan and add syrup.
Let boil 5 minutes.
Add sugar and flour mixture.
Add condensed milk.
Boil until finished. Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, well-greased with margarine.
When cool, cut and wrap in waxed paper.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Slice potatoes.
Layer potatoes and mixture until used up.

title: sunny carrot salad
directions: Combine tahini, juice from oranges and tamari soy sauce.
Stir until smooth.
Mix carrots and currants, then add tahini dressing.

title: chicken with cornmeal dumplings
directions: Put chicken and giblets in Dutch oven. Add carrots, onions and salt (to taste).
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Mix cornmeal, 1 teaspoon salt and baking powder. Beat eggs and milk together and add to cornmeal mixture until dough is stiff.
Add more cornmeal, if necessary. Remove chicken from broth, but keep warm. Drop dough by spoonful into boiling broth. Cover lightly and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve together.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and cocoa; cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Place by spoonfuls on waxed paper; cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding together with 3 cups liquid.
(Use liquid from canned fruits and add water to make remainder of 3 cups.)
Cool slightly, then add fruits.
Refrigerate.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Blend turkey with salt, thyme, pepper, egg, celery and onion until well blended.
Put in buttered pan.
Shape into loaf. Smooth top and sides with spatula.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until golden.
Before serving, arrange tomato slices and peppers over top.
Slice to serve.
For 8 servings, double recipe.

title: sugar cake
directions: Spray pan and press one can crescent rolls in pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Add the other can of crescent rolls on top of cream cheese mixture.
Make thumbprints on top of layer of crescent rolls to make wells.
Add brown sugar and melted butter to top layer.
Bake at 350° in sprayed 9 X 13 inch pan according to directions on crescent rolls package.

title: fried green tomatoes or squash
directions: Mix meal, salt and pepper; set aside.
Combine egg and water; beat well.
Dip tomato slices in egg mixture and dredge in cornmeal mix.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Chop onion in ground beef; brown and drain the grease.
Add salt, pepper, soup and garlic.
Stir in sour cream.
Cook noodles until tender; drain and then pour in meat.
Mix well.
Serve while hot.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: fresh dill pickles
directions: Wash pickles.
Place layer of dill on bottom of jar, then, layer some pickles; alternate.
Put in 2 to 3 garlic cloves. Bring 2 quarts water, salt and vinegar to a boil for a few minutes.
Pour this brine over the pickles and cover with white cloth over the jar; put in cool spot.
Let stand for 7 days.
Put in closed jar and refrigerate.

title: ozark mountain berry pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Stir in the berries, water and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat just to the boiling point.
Pour into pie shell.
Dot with the butter.
Lattice on full top crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Grocery store containers of fruit are enough to make 2 pies.)

title: blackberry bread(any fruit pulp)
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
(While hot, top with 1 cup powdered sugar, mixed with juice of 1 lemon, optional.)

title: twinkes or twinkles
directions: Mix and bake in long pan.
Cut in strips like Twinkies.
Put the following filling between slices.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and garlic in 1/4 cup oil.
Add rice and brown lightly.
Add chicken stock or broth and thawed spinach; stir well.
Add cheese.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes until rice is tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes well.
Place potatoes in large pot and boil (with skins on) until fork-tender.
Peel off skins and cut into small cubes.
Add all other ingredients and mix well while potatoes are still hot.
Chill several hours and serve on a bed of crisp lettuce with a garnish of tomato wedges.

title: cranberry pecan muffins
