directions: Combine coarsely chopped cranberries and 1/4 cup sugar in a small bowl; let stand while preparing batter.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and 1 cup sugar into a large bowl.
Cut in vegetable shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in chopped pecans and grated lemon rind.
Beat eggs in a small bowl until light; stir in milk.
Add liquid all at once to flour mixture, stirring just until moist.
Fold in cranberry mixture.
Spoon batter into greased medium-sized muffin cups, filling each 2/3 full.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with butter and honey.

title: cheesy-lime mold(blender)
directions: Put gelatin and boiling water in blender container.
Blend at low speed until gelatin is dissolved.
Add cream cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice to blender container; blend smooth. Halve cucumber lengthwise; remove seeds and cut in pieces.
Add cucumber and green pepper to blender container; blend until coarsely chopped.
Pour into 3 1/2 cup mold.
Yields 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: In a baking dish, spread the pineapple and pie filling evenly. Combine cake mix, coconut and pecans; sprinkle over mixture. Cover with thinly sliced margarine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: noodle, tuna, cream of celery soup casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in large baking bowl and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a medium bowl, combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onions; pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake uncovered for 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: political chili
directions: Heat oil in a 6 or 8-quart saucepan.
Add onions and cook until tender but not brown.
Add ground beef; sprinkle with chili powder, salt, paprika, Tabasco and oregano.
Cook meat until brown, breaking meat up with a fork as it cooks.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste, cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add beans and simmer 15 minutes more.
Yields 5 quarts.

title: jello dessert
directions: Make jello according to package instructions.
When partly set add egg whites.
Beat until all is foamy.
Refrigerate.
Make a custard of milk, egg yolks and sugar.
Cool and pour over jello in individual dishes.
Excellent for the small fry!

title: sloppy goulash
directions: Cut beef in 1/2-inch cubes.
Brown beef in hot oil.
Pour off excess oil.
Add can of tomatoes, cloves and Sloppy Joe mix. Cover loosely and simmer 1 hour.
Add sliced carrots.
Simmer 1/2 hour or until tender.
Serve over cooked noodles. Can be cooked in crock-pot.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Put oil in large pot and brown flour stirring constantly. Add onions, garlic and parsley and cook until seasonings are soft
Add peeled shrimp and cook until shrimp turns pink.
Add okra and keep stirring.
Cook another 5 minutes.
Add the can of tomatoes, then add about 1 1/2 quarts water.
Add bay leaf, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cook about 2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Marinate steaks or chicken at least 12 hours, turning often.

title: crunchy chip cookies
directions: Beat butter or margarine and sugars until creamy and fluffy; beat eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and noodles.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes 7 dozen.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy cook spaghetti(serves 4)
directions: Bring water to a boil; add margarine.
Add spaghetti.
Bring back to a boil.
Turn off fire.
Cover and let stand 15 minutes. Drain and do not rinse.
Serve with your favorite sauce.

title: leslie's cherry cheesecake
directions: Beat together powdered sugar, cream cheese and vanilla. Blend in Cool Whip. Put mixture in 2 graham cracker crusts. Cover with 1 can of pie filling. Sprinkle pecans on top of filling. Refrigerate for 4 hours. Serve.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop the corn and place in 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans, greased.
In saucepan, heat sugar, syrup, butter and salt until bubbling around the edge.
Heat 5 more minutes, stirring occasionally.
Take off heat and stir in baking soda until thick and foamy.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, mixing every 15 minutes. Becomes less sticky as it cools.
Clean up is simple.
I sometimes add plain peanuts.
Good also on apples.
Place apples on wax paper after dipping into caramel sauce.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Using your favorite cut of steak, generously apply meat tenderizer to both sides of meat.
Using meat cleaver, beat tenderizer into meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put desired amount of teriyaki sauce on both sides of steak.
Use meat cleaver or fork to work teriyaki sauce into meat.
Grill on medium or low. Delicious and tender!
If a grill is not available
to you, bake in oven at 350° until steak is done.
Turn meat only once.

title: mom's hearty vegetable soup
directions: Wash celery stalks and leaves; cut stalks in pieces.
Cut meat off bone and cut meat into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place meat and meat bone in saucepan.
Add water, salt, parsley, pepper and celery.
Cook gently 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Meanwhile, peel and dice potatoes.
Scrape carrots and cut in 1/2-inch pieces and peel and thinly slice onions.
Add vegetables to soup; continue to cook 1 hour longer or until vegetables are tender. Add tomatoes; cook soup 10 minutes longer.
Taste to correct seasonings and serve.

title: creamed onions
directions: Remove skins from whole onions.
Place in saucepan, adding 1 1/2 cups water and boil for 5 minutes.
Drain immediately; set onions aside.
In another saucepan make a white sauce by melting the butter.
Add flour and milk, stirring until it boils.
Add celery salt, parsley and cheese; mix well.
Put onions in a greased casserole, pouring the white sauce over them.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle a little grated cheese on top and reheat until lightly browned.

title: pink delight salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in jello. Let cool to room temperature.
Add cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: cookie sheet apple pie
directions: Mix flour, lard and salt.
Mix like a pie crust.
Put egg yolks in a measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 3/4 cup.
Add to flour mixture to make a soft dough.
Divide dough into 2 parts. Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Roll one part and fit in the bottom of cookie sheet.
Put dough on all sides.
Sprinkle 4 tablespoons tapioca on top of the dough.
Add the sliced apples on top of the dough.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add 1 box of Jiffy cornbread mix.
Cook at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cowboy beans
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Bake uncovered for 40 minutes at 375°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: garlic green beans
directions: Heat peanut oil in wok.
When hot, add garlic and ginger root. Cook for 1 minute.
Add beans, sugar, red pepper and fry, stirring constantly for 2 minutes.
Add soy sauce and vinegar. Cook for 2 minutes more and turn off heat.
Drizzle sesame oil into pan and toss with beans.
Can be quite spicy!

title: deviled eggs
directions: Place 12 fresh, uncracked eggs in pan and cover with cold water.

Bring to a boil and lightly cook on low for 18 minutes. The water should just barely boil.	Drain water and place eggs in ice water to cool.	Crack and peel shell from hard-boiled eggs. Cut in half lengthwise on cutting board.
Spoon out egg yolk and place in bowl.
Mash yolks with fork until fine.
Add salt, pepper, mayonnaise and sweet pickle relish.
Whip to creamy consistency.
Add Dijonnaise or prepared mustard and mix and whip again.
Taste and adjust according to your taste.
Pickle relish varies according to brands.
If you prefer a bit more sour, add an additional teaspoon or so of sweet pickle relish.
(Do not thin the mixture too much or the mixture will not mound nicely in the whites.)
The sweet pickle relish also serves to sweeten the mixture.
Fill whites with yolk mixture and sprinkle with paprika. Cover with plastic wrap and place in refrigerator.

title: apple roll-ups
directions: Remove rolls from package and slice apples equally to fit each roll.
Roll up.
Mix sugar and orange juice to dissolve.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Toast nuts in slow 325° oven until light brown. Fold sugar and salt into egg whites. Beat stiff. Fold nuts into meringue. Melt margarine in jelly roll pan. Spread nut mixture over margarine. Bake in 325° oven, stirring every 10 minutes, until nuts are coated and no margarine remains in pan. Cool. Yields 4 cups.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs and butter; pat firmly into 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy, add milk.
Beat until smooth and add eggs and vanilla. Mix well.

title: sherry's apricot fluff
directions: Mix together all ingredients and let set in refrigerator for 2 hours and it's ready to eat.

title: 3 bean bake
directions: Mix well; bake or heat until thoroughly hot.
A little bacon grease enhances the flavor.
Several hours on low in crock-pot works really great.
Great dish for potlucks.

title: chicken delight
directions: Wrap chicken breast with sliced beef.
Wrap 1 stick of bacon to each piece.
Mix soup and sour cream (may place in microwave so will mix easier).
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, for 3 hours at 300°.

title: guacamole-tomato salad
directions: Core tomatoes; scoop out centers and chop finely.
Sprinkle inside of tomato cups with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Turn upside down on paper towels and drain.
Chill.
To chopped tomato, add onion, green chilies to taste, lemon juice and remaining salt.
Chill.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie pan.
Cook and stir beef and onion in skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick until smooth.
Pour into plate over beef.
Add tomato sauce.
Bake 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake about 8 minutes more. Cool 5 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine gelatin and cake mix.
Add eggs and oil.
Blend together. Add strawberries and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into a 4 x 8 or 3 x 9-inch prepared cake pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove and cool.

title: pesto
directions: *Or Parmesan and Romano
Parmesan
to 1/4 Romano) with Romano optional (fresh, not packaged).

title: willie's dirty rice
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together and pour over meat.
If using pork
chops:
brown
chops and put in baking dish.	Pour rice mixture
over
chops and bake covered for 1 hour at 350°. If using chicken:
place
chicken
pieces
in baking dish and pour rice mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Can use chicken broth instead of consomme.
Dirty Rice can be baked without meat and used as a side dish if desired.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Boil the Karo syrup and sugar until smooth and creamy. Add the cornflakes until covered.
Place in baking pan and let cool.

title: pork and bean bread
directions: Pour water over raisins and set aside.

title: pecan carrots
directions: Wash and cut carrots into 1/2-inch slices.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole with butter and brown sugar.
Cover and cook in microwave 10 minutes.
Mix water and cornstarch until smooth. Stir into carrot mixture.
Add pecans; cover and continue to cook 6 minutes.

title: cranberry pork roast
directions: Place pork in crock-pot.
Mash cranberries, sugar, cranberry juice, mustard and cloves and pour over roast.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Remove roast and keep warm.
Skim fat.
Measure 2 cups juice, add water if necessary and put in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, add cornstarch and water paste and cook until thickened. Season with salt.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bell pepper casserole(shared by jewell isaacs)
directions: Clean peppers and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Blanch in boiling water 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove peppers; reserve liquid.
Grease casserole dish.
Layer peppers, then cheese, then crushed crackers.
Repeat.
Use enough of the reserved liquid to make the crackers soften up.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together in 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Place in baking dish and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Toast bread.
Place in casserole dish 9 x 13-inch (6 slices will fit on one layer.)
Add another layer of toast.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over bread.
Dish should stand for a few minutes to soak.
Set a saucer on top to hold down bread. Put remaining pats of butter on top.
Soak for 3 to 4 hours or refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until bread puffs up and is golden brown.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix and freeze.
For more color you can add red food coloring (is pretty for Christmas).
Cuts into squares nicely for serving.

title: lemon curd filling
directions: Combine lemon juice and rind, sugar and butter in a heavy saucepan.
Place over low heat until mixture is boiling and sugar is dissolved.
Beat yolks and eggs until combined.
While beating, pour a little of the boiling liquid into eggs; mix well.
Return all to heavy saucepan, put over low heat and stir with whisk until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and continue stirring 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Pour into quart jar and cool. Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep for months.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream the flour, butter and confectioners sugar.
Press mixture evenly in bottom of ungreased square pan. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: orange-buttermilk summer salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
When mixture boils, add the gelatin and stir until dissolved, then let cool slightly; stir in buttermilk. Chill until partially set.
Fold in whipped topping and nuts. Chill until mixture mounds.
Pour into a lightly oiled mold, 8 1/2 cups in size or larger.
Chill overnight.

title: ingredients cookies
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Sprinkle in layers: graham cracker crumbs, butterscotch, chocolate chips and coconut.
Spread condensed milk over top and then sprinkle on nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut in small squares.

title: hello dollies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch pan melt butter. Sprinkle crumbs over the melted butter.
Pour in condensed milk. Spread evenly.
Top with remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely before cutting.
Store loosely in covered container at room temperature.

title: jane brody's shrimp sauce(yum, yum!)
directions: Cut the shrimp in half lengthwise.
Heat the oil in a medium skillet.
Add the onion, garlic and shrimp and saute the ingredients, stirring, until the shrimp turn pink, about 5 minutes.
Remove the shrimp and set them aside.
Add the tomatoes and juice, black pepper, cayenne, basil and salt to the skillet. Bring the mixture to a boil, reduce the heat and simmer it, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add the shrimp and parsley to the tomato mixture and serve the sauce over 3/4 pound of pasta with sprinkled Parmesan, if desired.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn and half of the crumbled bacon.
Add the onion and bell pepper and put in casserole dish.
Mix the other half of the bacon with the bread crumbs and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bread crumbs brown.

title: hot sauce
directions: Cut off stems and remove seeds from peppers.
Put in pan with onions and tomatoes.
Cook until thick.
Fill hot, sterilized jars.
Seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower and cooked rice in a flat baking dish.
Pour mushroom soup over mixture, stirring to mix soup throughout mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Put Cheez Whiz over mixture and bake 10 more minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook the chicken and cut up into small pieces. Cook broccoli, then drain all the water out.
Mix chicken and broccoli in a pan. Put aside.
In mixing bowl, put soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Melt butter and put bread crumbs into melted butter.
Mix until it looks like graham cracker crumbs.
Put over chicken and broccoli.
Cover with foil. Bake in oven at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Serve over noodles or rice. Serves 6 people.

title: grandma's frosting
directions: Blend milk and flour until smooth.
Cook until thick.
Cool. Cream butter for 4 minutes.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Cream for 4 minutes.
Add flour mixture.
Beat for 4 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together soup, broth, chilies and pepper.
Set aside. Soften tortillas by dipping one at a time in hot oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Mix chicken and onion.
Put about 2 tablespoons chicken mixture on center of tortilla.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and roll up.
Place in shallow baking dish and pour soup mixture over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
(Water may be used instead of vegetable oil to soften tortillas; they will be soft, but not oily.)

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil and cook to the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla, nuts and margarine.
Beat until cool and pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, butter and evaporated milk in saucepan and bring to boil. Cook 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, marshmallows and vanilla and blend thoroughly. Pour into a greased pan and cool. Cut into squares.

title: banana split cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Spread on bottom of dish.

title: party rye bread
directions: Mix these ingredients together well.
Spread on buttered party rye bread.
Sprinkle Bac*Os over each one and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Put 1/4 the amount in bottom of pie shell.
Put in peaches, arranging slices close together. Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture over peaches.
Pour cream over all.
Strip top with pastry.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 375° to finish baking (about 45 minutes).

title: cucumber rye
directions: Mix together and spread mixture on rye snack bread.
Put thin slice of unpeeled cucumber on top and sprinkle with lemon pepper.

title: creme de menthe bars
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Mix well; press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: blackberry frozen yogurt
directions: Thaw berries, if frozen.
Meanwhile, in medium saucepan, combine sugar and gelatin; stir in milk and 1/4 water.
Heat just until gelatin dissolves.
Set aside to cool.

title: smothered chicken (old-fashioned way)
directions: *I like the lite Cajun seasonings instead of salt and pepper.

title: lemon ice box cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 5 layers or in 2 layers and split into 4 layers.
While cake is baking mix condensed milk and lemon juice. Put into refrigerator to cool.
When cake layers are done and cooled, spread condensed milk mixture between layers, reserving 1/2 c. mixture.
Mix reserved mixture with cool whip.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Store in refrigerator.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and put into blender.
Add cream cheese and sour cream. Blend until smooth.
Pour into large bowl and mix in cool whip. Pour into crust.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix beef and pork.
Add cooked rice, salt and pepper.
Hollow out peppers and stuff.
Place in large Dutch oven pan.
Pour soup and water in.
Cook over medium heat until boiling, then lower heat.
Peppers are done when peppers are soft and meat tastes done, about an hour and a half.
Add sour cream to soup when peppers are cooked and done.

title: chocolate-oat bars
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Stir in egg and vanilla. Add oats, flour, baking soda and salt.
Press 2/3 of mixture into greased, 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Melt chocolate chips, sweetened condensed milk and butter, stirring constantly over low heat.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour over mixture in baking pan. Crumble remaining oat mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly; cut into squares.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Fill large pot 3/4 of the way full with water.
Bring to boil on high heat.
Add spaghetti.
Boil until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Put spaghetti back in pot and add sauce.
Stir until well blended.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Mix together and chill for several hours before serving.
This will keep for a week.

title: overnight sticky buns(good for breakfast!)
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt cake pan.
Place frozen rolls in pan. Mix brown sugar and pudding mix (not instant).
Sprinkle over rolls.
Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over brown sugar and pudding mix.
Spread pecans over this.
Pour melted butter over pecans.
Place on cabinet overnight.
Do not cover! (May cover lightly with a towel.)

title: spiced tea
directions: Simmer for about 2 hours before serving.
Do not boil.

title: enchiladas
directions: Shred cheeses and reserve 1/3 of mixture.
Combine cumin and 1 cup of picante sauce.
Combine with cheese mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Spoon mixture into shells and roll up; place seam side down.
Spoon reserved picante sauce over top and sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix ground chuck, milk and bread crumbs together and form into balls.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Don't cover while baking.

title: company baked beans
directions: Chop bacon into small pieces; lightly brown in skillet.
Add green pepper and onion; continue to cook until tender.
Add all other ingredients; stir to blend.
Pour bean mixture into lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: mom's vinegar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour in crust and bake. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: ricky's beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Save most of drippings.
Saute onion in same pan.
Add rest of ingredients including bacon and simmer until thick.
If desired, sprinkle on cheese until melted.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and spices into medium mixing bowl.
Add sugar, shortening, egg and milk to first mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add oats and raisins; mix well. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased baking sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spinach and pasta pie
directions: Combine eggs, cooked pasta, 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Spread mixture over bottom and up sides of a greased 9-inch pie plate to form a shell.
Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well.
Mix together spinach, Ricotta cheese and nutmeg.
Spoon into pasta-lined plate.
Spread remaining spaghetti sauce atop filling.
Cover edge of pie with foil.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake 5 more minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: hillary clinton's cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Beat together shortening, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs, beating until fluffy.
Beat in flour and oats.
Stir in chips.

title: sopapillas bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Let raise in covered bowl for at least 2 to 3 hours.
Then roll dough about 1/8-inch thick.
Then cut into squares or as big as you want them. Fry in Fry Daddy or at 375°.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Puree zucchini.
There should be 1 1/2 cups.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch metal baking pan.
In large bowl, mix zucchini, flour and remaining ingredients, except walnuts.
Beat at low speed until just mixed.
Increase speed to high; beat 2 minutes or until smooth.
Stir in walnuts.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix baking powder and flour.
Add to egg mixture.
Heat milk and butter to boiling point and add to batter; beat well.
Pour in oblong pan that has been greased in bottom only and not floured. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate caramels
directions: Put all ingredients into a kettle and boil until it hardens when dropped into cold water.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Turn into greased tins.
When nearly cold, cut into small squares.

title: carrot snack cups
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin with lemon juice, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Fold in carrots; spoon into individual glasses.
Chill until set, about 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Microwave Directions:
Sprinkle both sides of chicken with taco seasoning mix.
Place chicken in 8-inch square microwave-safe baking dish.
Pour salsa over chicken.
Cover with waxed paper. Microwave on High for 5 to 9 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and juices run clear, rotating dish once halfway through cooking.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese; microwave on High for 45 to 60 seconds or until cheese melts.
Serve with sour cream.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs until light and foamy. Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add vanilla and milk.
Mix until smooth and chill.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick and cut into desired shapes.
May sprinkle with sugar.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove.
Let stand at room temperature 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cabbage creole
directions: Fry bacon in skillet.
Take bacon out on paper towels; set aside.
Cut up cabbage, onions and bell pepper and cook about 10 minutes into some of the bacon drippings.
Add tomatoes, salt and crumbled bacon into mixture.
Cook about 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sister-in-law's easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Cut crusts from bread and cut each piece into five fingers. Place bread over fruit.
Mix sugar, flour, egg, vanilla and butter (melted).
Pour over fruit and bread fingers.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: congealed salad
directions: Pour hot water over Jell-O.
Stir until mixed well.
Chill until it begins to thicken.
Mix other ingredients and add to Jell-O.
Put in refrigerator until set.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough in 1/8-inch slices.
Line a 14-inch pizza pan with slices overlapping slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Cool.
Blend softened cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar and vanilla. Spread over cookie crust.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese.
Use any combination of fresh or drained, canned fruit.
Glaze with marmalade or preserves mixed with water.
Chill.

title: sugar candy
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the Karo, water and sugar until it reaches 280° on a candy thermometer.
Add 1 tsp. flavoring and 1 tsp. coloring and pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
When hard, break into bite- size pieces.
Suggested flavorings:
mint, orange, cherry, lime

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and cut shortening into flour. Add milk to make soft dough.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead lightly for 1 minute.
Roll out, cut out biscuits and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: brown sugar icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Sift flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt together about 3 times.
Add to first mixture and blend.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Shape into a roll (or rolls) about an inch in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Slice very thin; bake on greased cookie sheet in a 300° oven until golden brown.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Halve
the hard-boiled eggs and remove yolks.
Into the yolks, add
all
ingredients.
Spoon
into
egg white halves. Sprinkle with a little paprika.
You may wish to decorate each half with a sliced olive (black or green).
Ready to serve.

title: granny's buttermilk pie
directions: Mix
sugar, flour and butter.
Add eggs, buttermilk and flavoring.	Pour
in 9-inch unbaked crust.	Bake 10 minutes at 450°; then reduce heat to 350° for 35 minutes.

title: apple crisp pudding (german)
directions: Combine apples, water and cinnamon in 7 x 13 inch baking dish.
Combine margarine, flour and sugar; cut until mixture becomes crumbly and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: pork fajitas
directions: Mix lime juice, 1 tablespoon oil, the garlic, hot pepper sauce, cumin and salt in a plastic food storage bag.
Add pork; close bag and turn to coat.
Let stand at room temperature 20 minutes.

title: cajun chicken over rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic powder; set aside. Combine tomatoes and remaining ingredients, except rice, in a large Dutch oven. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Add chicken and return to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until tender. Serve over rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Set aside.
Mix cake mix with 3/4 cup melted oleo and 3/4 cup evaporated milk. Spread 1/2 of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan that has been sprayed with Pam or lightly greased.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Then spread melted caramel mix on cake.
Then sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on cake.
Spread remaining cake mix over this and bake 18 to 20 minutes longer at 350°.
Let cool before cutting. The remaining cake mix will not cover the caramels and nuts completely.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Heavily butter one casserole dish.
Dust sides and bottom of dish with cracker crumbs.
Then line bottom of dish with about 1/4-inch cracker crumbs.
Save remaining cracker crumbs to cover top of casserole.

title: spanish rice
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Pour off half the fat.
In remaining fat, cook onion and green pepper until tender. Add tomatoes, water, rice, chili sauce, salt, brown sugar, etc. Cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Crumble bacon over top. Serves 6.

title: leftover stir-fry(portuguese)
directions: Mix chicken broth, cornstarch, soy sauce, sugar and garlic. Set aside.
Heat frying pan or wok and coat with vegetable oil. Add frozen vegetables.
Stir-fry until tender (about 2 minutes). Add meat. Stir-fry 1 minute. Stir in broth mix.
Cook and stir until thickened. Serve over rice.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350°.
Makes 2 or 3 eight-inch layers.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours prior to serving.

title: minestrone
directions: Wash and chop carrots, celery, onion, pared potato and zucchini.
Mince garlic.
Coarsely shred cabbage.
Heat oil and butter in Dutch oven or big pot over medium heat.
Saute onions until soft and golden, 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir in carrots and potatoes; saute 5 minutes.
Stir in celery and green beans; saute 5 minutes.
Stir in zucchini; saute 3 minutes.
Then cabbage and garlic; cook 1 minute.

title: pie
directions: Put oleo in pie pan.
Melt in oven.
Add flour and sugar.
Mix together and pat in pan up sides.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix together all of measured ingredients and knead for 10 minutes by hand.
Rest 5 minutes.
Split dough in half.
Roll dough out on counter or flat surface to about 1/2-inch thick.
Brush or pat margarine (melted) over surface of rolled dough.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except crackers and butter.
Crush crackers and put melted oleo on crackers.
Sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese rolls
directions: In large bowl, mix cream cheese, onion salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix until ingredients are softened.
Slice pickles into little cubes; add to mixture.
Mix well.
On each slice of ham, spread mixture evenly.
Roll ham; hold with toothpicks.
Cut into slices.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add it to well-mixed sugar and flour, set aside. Beat eggs and add them, along with the butter, to the juice mix. Cook this mixture over medium heat until it thickens. Watch closely and lower heat, if needed, so it doesn't scorch or burn, stirring constantly. Cool; add to pineapple. Fold in marshmallows, nuts and bananas. Mix well before serving. Keep refrigerated.
Serves: 12-15.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except the potato chips and cheese.
Put in oiled 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with the potato chips mixed with the cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated. Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: jac-pac's ham salad
directions: Mix all ingredients by using your hand.
Makes salad taste better.

title: cheese ball
directions: *To make cheese ball put in 1 cup of pecans and roll the ball in the other cup.

title: chicken soup
directions: In a 3-quart pan, combine butter, onion and garlic, stirring over medium heat until onion is soft, about 8 minutes. Stir in flour and gradually add the broth and bring to a boil on high heat. Add potato and cover. Simmer over low heat until potato is tender, about 15 to 20 minutes. Add cooked chicken; cover and simmer until chicken is well heated. Add basil or other herbs. Use cheese, if desired.

title: warm mulled wine with aromatic spices
directions: Cut oranges in half.
Stud each half with 4 cloves.
Bring 2 cups water to boil in heavy, large nonaluminum saucepan.
Add orange halves, sugar and 6 cinnamon sticks; stir over medium-high heat until sugar dissolves.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add wine. Adjust heat so that mixture is almost simmering and cook for 20 minutes; do not boil.
Remove orange halves and cinnamon sticks from wine.
Ladle wine into mugs.
Attach orange slice to rim of each mug.
Garnish each with cinnamon stick and serve.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter candy
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and roll into small balls.
In top of double boiler, melt chocolate chips and wax. Dip balls into chocolate mixture with toothpick.
Place on wax paper and cool.

title: dirty rice
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Saute mushrooms and rice until rice is brown.
Add soup and 1 cup water plus juice from mushrooms.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes until moisture is absorbed.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine the coconut and milk.
Add vanilla and mix thoroughly. Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° (180° C) oven for about 10 minutes.
Remove from sheet immediately when the macaroons are cooked.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Brown onion and celery in margarine.
Add all ingredients except cheese in buttered 2-quart dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread cheese over top and bake 15 minutes more.
If you use another rice, you need to cook it.

title: polish pastry
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients as for pie crust.
Make 1 roll.
Wrap in waxed paper or other wrap and refrigerate overnight.
(Can be kept in refrigerator for 2 or 3 days.) The next day, divide the roll into 5 sections. Roll one piece at a time as for a 9 or 10-inch pie.
Cut this into 8 pieces (triangles).
Place 1/2 teaspoon preserves at wide edge and roll.
Place seam side down on ungreased baking sheet. Bend to form crescent. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: old fashioned apple cake
directions: Cream sugar with shortening; add egg.
Sift flour with soda and salt, add to cream mixture alternating with milk and apples. Add walnuts, vanilla and cinnamon, mix well.
Pour batter into a lightly greased and floured 13 X 9 inch pan.

title: fish chowder
directions: Add green pepper, celery and diced onion to pan with little oil and saute.
Add 1/2 cup water, potato, fish, corn and seasonings and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and heat until hot; do not boil.
May add a little butter and smoke, if you like.
I like a little more milk.

title: cauliflower in wine
directions: Melt butter in large, heavy frying pan; add cauliflower, celery and onion.
Combine bouillon cube, wine, salt and pepper; pour over vegetables.
Cook quickly over high heat, turning constantly.
Cook until vegetables are barely tender and still crisp, about 7 or 8 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: broccoli with pimiento cheese sauce
directions: Cook
broccoli according to package directions, arrange in shallow
buttered
1/2-quart
casserole.
Combine soup, butter, lemon juice, cheese and pimientos;
spoon over broccoli.
Top with crackers and pecans.
Bake until heated through.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Boil butter, sugar, milk and cocoa on stove for 2 minutes. Remove from heat; add peanut butter and oats.
Stir.
Drop spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Wait to cool.
Enjoy.

title: cheesy peas
directions: Drain peas.
Cook Cheez Whiz until melted, then pour over peas in buttered baking dish.
Add chopped eggs. Stir to blend.
Top with onions.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add yolks, 1 at a time, beating well after each. Blend in vanilla and chocolate.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in beaten whites. Pour in 3 (9-inch) pans lined on bottoms with paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Butter Bundt cake pan.
Put half of nuts and raisins in bottom of pan, then put in rolls.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients (except butter) on top of rolls.
Slice butter on top.
Allow to thaw and rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, then turn upside down and remove from
pan immediately.

title: chocolate kilarney pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add melted margarine and mix well.
Add eggs and mix.
Add vanilla and mix.
Pour into pie shell and bake approximately 30 minutes in a 325° oven.
Pie will appear shaky in center, but will firm up as it sits.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken.
Pour hot water from chicken over broccoli and let stand while preparing sauce.
Butter 2 1/2 or 3 quart baking dish.
Layer broccoli and chicken.
Pour sauce over top.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Top with buttered bread crumbs before putting in oven.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain juice from pears.
Heat pear juice until hot.
Add Jell-O, turn down to low so Jell-O won't burn.
Add room temperature cream cheese to juice until melted.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Let gel until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Mix cake mix with eggs and lemon extract. Add Jell-O mixture.
Pour into greased, floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add 1/2 cup parsley and nuts along with remaining ingredients.
Form into ball and roll in remaining nuts and parsley.

title: peach (or apple) cobbler
directions: Cook
fruit and sugar with a little water until tender. Pour fruit with syrup into baking dish.	Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix with fork until crumbly.
Spread
over
fruit.
This will sink into dish.
Pour melted butter on
top.
Bake
at
375° for 40 minutes.
The crumb mixture will rise to top of pan and brown.

title: delicious potatoes
directions: Place in a greased casserole.
Top with buttered corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable rice
directions: Put butter in frying pan and melt.
Cut up mushrooms, onion and peppers.
Put them in frying pan and cover until soft.
Boil 2 1/4 cups water and add 4 bouillon cubes to it.
Stir.
Then pour in frying pan with vegetables.
Add rice.
Keep covered.
Cook 30 minutes on low heat.

title: dieter's delight
directions: Using a wire whisk, blend pineapple and yogurt together. Slowly blend in sugar-free vanilla pudding, stirring all the time. Divide into 1/2 cup servings.
Add a tablespoon of Cool Whip when serving.
Enjoy.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Chop chocolate and cube butter.
Melt over double boiler.
Add sugar and coffee.
Mix well to combine.
Cool until just warm. Whisk the eggs together and then add to chocolate mixture.
Whisk well.
Pour into a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan that has been greased and dusted with sugar.
Bake at 325° until set.
Cool then refrigerate.
Release pan sides.
Garnish with sweetened whipped cream and semi-sweet chocolate curls.

title: microwave macaroni and cheese
directions: Place margarine in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave at High (100%) until melted.
Blend in flour, salt, mustard, pepper and pepper sauce.
Stir in milk.
Microwave at High (100%) until thickened, blending with wire whisk once or twice.
Stir in cheese.
Microwave at High (100%) to soften cheese.
Stir in macaroni.

title: eggplant, bacon spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti enough for four.
In a large skillet brown bacon and add garlic and onion.
Let cook for 1 minute.
Add eggplant; cook until done.
Add tomato and mushrooms; cook for 1 minute.
In a small saucepan add 1 to 1 1/2 cups water.
Add Ramen or saimin flavor packet.
Thicken sauce with flour or cornstarch.
Place spaghetti on platter; pour on bacon and vegetable mix, then sauce. Serve hot.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Generously grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows over bottom of pan.
Combine Jell-O (dry) with strawberries and set aside.
In a large bowl, blend rest of ingredients until moist, then beat for 3 minutes on medium speed. Pour batter evenly over marshmallows in pan.
Now pour strawberry mixture evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until golden and toothpick comes out clean.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.
As the cake bakes the strawberries sink and the marshmallows rise and glaze the top.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Add salt and flour.
Knead until smooth. Cover and let rise about 15 minutes. Divide dough into 16 portions. Roll each into narrow rolls and shape pretzels. Dip each pretzel in soda solution and sprinkle with salt.
Place on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: spinach cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a buttered casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: magnificent meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a shallow pan.
Shape into a loaf. Bake at 350° for one hour. Pour off drippings.
Add tomato sauce and 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: night before casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: microwave bread and butter pickles
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine all ingredients. Microwave covered with plastic wrap on High 8 to 10 minutes, stirring twice, until cucumbers are tender-crisp.
Ladle into glass jars and refrigerate.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: homemade chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook one minute.
Add broth, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Place one pie crust in a greased 9 x 9-inch square baking dish with tall sides.
Pour in filling.
Top with second crust, sealing around the edges.
Make several slits in top crust with a knife.
Brush with melted butter, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until top is browned.
Let cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: blueberry icebox pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend in sugar.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Fold Dream Whip into cream cheese sugar mixture.
Slice bananas and place over bottom of crust.
Sprinkle lemon juice over bananas.
Spoon cream mixture into crust over bananas.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Can be garnished with Dream Whip, then refrigerated.

title: weight watchers icebox snickers
directions: Take 2 heaping cups of patience, 1 heart full of love and 2 handfuls of generosity. Add a dash of laughter and 1 head full of understanding.
1 can cream of chicken soup

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with foil.
Put rice in bottom with 1 cup milk.
Lay on chicken pieces.
(I use 6 to 8 chicken breasts instead of whole chicken.)
Sprinkle seasonings and onion soup on top.
Pour soup and 1 cup milk (mixed) over chicken. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: buttermilk lemon pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and add sugar. Beat well. Spread on top of pie and bake at 350 degrees until golden brown. Cool for 1 hour then refrigerate for at least 5 hours more.

title: cherry angel roll
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Line 2 loaf pans with foil (bottom). Pour batter into pans and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: campfire beans
directions: Brown meat with onion. Drain meat of excess grease. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from heat. Will serve 10 to 12 adults.

title: lemon lush
directions: Crush pecans.
Pour in melted butter and flour.
Mix well and pour into a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spanish rice tortilla pie
directions: Cook rice according to directions, but only cook 10 minutes. Brown ground meat lightly, but do not cook through.
Drain any excess fat, add rice.
Stir in tomato paste, cumin, water, onion and salt, mixing all ingredients well.
Portion about 1/3 of mixture into 8 1/2 x 1 x 2-inch (2-quart) glass baking dish.
Lay one tortilla over top, tucking sides in as required. Repeat the layers with the remaining mixture and tortillas.
Spread salsa evenly over the top of the final layer, sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Cover with foil; bake in a 400° preheated oven for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serve warm. Serves 6.

title: spaghetti sauce(crock-pot)
directions: Mix all together; heat to boiling. Then put in slow cooker and cook all day.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef and onions; drain.
Mix in soup and Cheez Whiz.
Spread in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover top with frozen Tater Tots and cook according to directions on Tater Tot package.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Beat egg, add milk and add this to cornmeal mixture.
Add onion and red pepper.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in 2-quart casserole and cover. Bake at 400° until bubbly hot, about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate layer dessert
directions: Press in bottom of 9 x 13 pan or glass casserole dish. Bake 20 - 25 minutes at 350.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg. Mix all dry ingredients together. Add to sugar mixture. Add blueberries; stir. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: ten minute delight(makes 2 pies)
directions: Bake pastry shells at 350° until brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip until smooth.
Add nuts. Fill shells with this mixture.
Top each cheese mixture with prepared pie filling.
Refrigerate until cold before serving.

title: ritzy broccoli or veggie casserole
directions: Cook broccoli or veggies 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese; mix well.
Add veggies and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
May be frozen before baked.

title: corn dog bites
directions: Combine flour, meal and sugar.
Combine 2 tablespoons oil, egg and milk.
Stir into flour mixture.
Cut hot dogs into pieces. Dip in batter and fry in hot oil until brown.
Serve with mustard or ketchup.

title: shrimp-corn-sausage toss
directions: Fill large stew pot halfway with water.
Add can of beer and shrimp crab bag and bring to a full boil; drop in corn and boil 20 minutes.
Add sausage and bring to full boil for 10 minutes. Lastly, add shrimp and cook 2 minutes, drain and serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together salad dressing mix and sour cream with wire whisk.
Mix water chestnuts, onion and thawed and drained spinach and add to salad dressing.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: portuguese clams(ameijoas portuguesas)
directions: Halve garlic and saute it lightly in oil.
When hot add clams which have been thoroughly rinsed several times in water.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with tight lid and steam until clams open.
Add lemon juice and parsley.
Then shake pan to distribute and leave over heat for a few minutes longer.
Serve piping hot with lemon wedges and slices of bread.
Makes 4 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in half.
Dip in butter.
Layer in greased bread pan, sprinkling each layer with sugar and cinnamon.
Fill pan 3/4 full.
Bake at 425°, until golden brown on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Reserve 1 cup Ritz crackers for topping.
Put into casserole dish and sprinkle 1 cup Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out dough 1/8 inch thick.
Cut in 7-inch squares.

title: butter-me-not rolls
directions: Cut butter into flour with pastry blender.
Add sour cream. Mix until smooth.
Drop by spoonful into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Can bake in miniature muffin cups for party rolls.
Good to serve with a salad plate.

title: pea pickin' cake
directions: Substitute oranges with juice for the liquid required in the cake mix.
Bake the cake according to directions.
Invert after ten minutes.
Mix the pudding, pineapple and whipped topping. Spread one-half of the mixture between the cooled layers of the cake and the remaining on top of the cake.
Sprinkle with walnuts.

title: waffles
directions: Make batter night before.
Mix with mixer.
Heat waffle iron up.
Put 2/3 cup in griddle.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt all ingredients in a saucepan.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour after mixed.
Roll dough into walnut shape, roll in sugar, place on a cookie sheet and bake for 7 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: easy boat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until cheese has melted and dip is warm.
Do not boil.

title: fresh summer tart
directions: Press cookie dough onto greased 14-inch pizza pan or into two 8-inch tart pans and bake according to directions.
Cool.
Beat cheese, sugar and 2 tablespoons of Triple Sec until fluffy. Spread over cooled crust.
Arrange fruit decoratively on crust. Melt jelly with remaining 2 tablespoons Triple Sec and brush over fruit to glaze.
Cut in wedges.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Bring chicken broth to a slow boil.
Add remainder of ingredients until tortellini is cooked, approximately 10 minutes.

title: judy's fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding a little milk, if necessary, to bring to dipping consistency.
Chill.
Serve with pieces of fruit.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pie filling and pineapple into a long glass baking dish. Mix together.
Sprinkle coconut on top of cake mix.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Add pecans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: broccoli mandarin orange salad
directions: Toss dressing with remaining combined ingredients in serving bowl.
Serve chilled.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: marie's green tomato relish
directions: Put tomatoes, onion, and peppers in a large pot; mix remaining ingredients together and pour over tomatoes. Heat just until it begins to boil; remove from heat and pack in sterile jars; seal immediately.

title: ham or chicken puffs
directions: Bring water and margarine to boil.
Add flour, and stir.
It will have the consistency of Play Dough.
Stir about 1 minute. Take off stove.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
(You may need to add a little flour to make it a good drop consistency.)
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cut each roll in two pieces; stuff with ham salad or chicken salad.

title: filipino barbecue
directions: Cut pork into cubes.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over pork.
Marinate 6 hours.
Thread onto skewers and grill.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix half the Cool Whip in with the condensed milk.
Add the sour cream and Tang.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Put the other half of the Cool Whip on top of the pie.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with beef.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Arrange in prepared dish.
Top with bacon.
Combine sour cream and soup in bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Cut round steak in large squares.
Sprinkle
generously with Lawry's
seasoned
salt.
Spread generous amount of prepared mustard over meat.	Place some diced bacon and onion on meat
and roll-up; tie with string or use toothpicks to hold. Brown
small amount
of bacon and onion in frying pan.
Place rolled
meat in pan and brown.
Once browned, cover with water and	simmer	for approximately
hour.
Thicken
gravy with cornstarch.

title: cheezy dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs vertical and then in half again. Fry hot dogs in frying pan. Right before they are done, add shredded cheese on top. Let melt. Serve immediately.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In a large pot combine first 5 ingredients to water; cook until chicken is done.
Remove chicken and let cool.
Discard skin and bones.
Cube chicken and return to pot.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Cook until almost done.
Make dumplings from recipe on box.
Drop dumplings into simmering pot.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.

title: ham and broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease bottom of a 13x9 pan. Unroll crescent rolls, spread across bottom of pan.
Spread broccoli on top of rolls.
Sprinkle ham on top of broccoli. Sprinkle cheeses on top of ham.
Mix together the eggs and milk. Stir until mixed together.
Pour milk mixture over the broccoli, ham and cheese.
Bake for 35-45 minutes or until done.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add dry ingredients and oats.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together in food processor.
Mix in small intervals so as not to chop meat too small.
Make into a ball and roll in walnuts.

title: harvest sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
In a bowl, combine the potatoes, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In another bowl, lightly beat the eggs, milk and butter.
Add to the sweet potato
mixture and combine well.
Pour the mixture into the pie shell.
Bake in the center of the oven for 45 minutes or until the tip of a knife comes out clean when tested.

title: old-fashioned bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain, discarding soaking water. Combine all ingredients in slow cooker.
Cover.
Cook on high 8 to 9 hours.
Debone ham bone; cut meat into bite-sized pieces and stir back into soup.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pot roast
directions: Wrap chuck roast in aluminum foil with onion soup mix spread over top of meat.
Roast in oven at 350° for 30 minutes per pound.

title: basil chicken
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour and 1 teaspoon basil.
Coat chicken lightly with flour mixture.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Cook broccoli.
Cook rice.

title: sweetheart pudding
directions: Boil together the milk, sugar, egg yolks, flour and vanilla. Cool.
Mix cracker crumbs, butter and 1/4 cup sugar.
Keep out some crumbs to put on top.
Line pan with crumbs and pour in pudding.
Beat egg whites.
Add a little sugar, vanilla and cream of tartar.
Put on top of pudding.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until nicely browned.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Grind ham, pepper and cheese (or grate cheese).
Combine with rest of ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peach pizza
directions: Blend flour, butter, brown sugar and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: poultry bread stuffing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until onions are pearly.
Add spices to taste.
Mix well.
Add a few cups of water, depending on how large your bird is.
Bring to full boil.
Take off heat. Slowly add bread or croutons, stirring well, don't allow mixture to become dry.
Cool.
Stuff your bird.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in nuts. Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Gradually add sugar and cook for 2 minutes.
Stir a couple of times.
Remove from heat and beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in nut and flour mixture.
Add chocolate chips, if using.

title: seafood jambalaya
directions: Place all ingredients in rice cooker (raw); mix well.
When rice cooker turns off, stir and turn on again until done.

title: upside-down coffeecake
directions: Grease and flour a 9-inch square baking pan. Spread jelly evenly onto bottom of pan.
Prepare cake batter according to package directions. Stir in 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 cup chocolate chips.

Pour batter over jelly layer, spreading gently and evenly. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup chips over top. Bake 50 to 55 minutes in a 325° oven until cake springs back when touched lightly. Cool 5 minutes in pan.
Invert onto serving plate. Cool at least 15 minutes. Serve warm.
Yields 9 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into casserole dish (sprayed with nonstick spray).
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: easy shrimp creole
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and celery in butter until slightly cooked, about 5 minutes.
Add and blend flour.
Combine with tomatoes, salt, pepper, sugar and bay leaf.
Cook gently for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Add shrimp and Worcestershire sauce. Serve plain or over cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: texas white chili
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil and add cumin, oregano, coriander, cloves, and cayenne.
Let cook together until onions are clear.
Cook over medium heat so your garlic doesn't burn. Add beans, broth and salt.
Let come to a simmer.
Smash half beans.
Add cooked shredded chicken and green chilies.
Stir together and let simmer 20 minutes.
Spoon into bowls and top with shredded cheese and sliced green onions.
Serve with jalapeno or cheese corn bread.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Marinate wings 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be frozen after marinating before cooking.
While baking, pour some of the sauce over wings for more flavor.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Combine crumbs and some butter on bottom of dish, then alternate all ingredients, ending with crumbs and butter on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon pudding cheese pie
directions: Blend cheese with 1/2 cup milk.
Add pudding mix.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk and blend slowly until well mixed (about 1 minute).
Pour at once into pie shell.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Chill 1 hour or until well set.
Serve with a spoonful of cherry pie filling.

title: crisp chocolate truffles
directions: In heavy 2 qt. saucepan, combine marshmallow cream, margarine and chocolate chips. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth; remove from heat. Stir cereal into hot chocolate mixture mixing until thoroughly combined. Drop by rounded measuring teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper lined baking sheet. Refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour. In top of double boiler, over hot water, melt white coating and shortening. Dip each chocolate ball in coating and place on waxed paper lined baking sheet. Decorate with sprinkles, if desired. Refrigerate until firm. Place in small candy paper cups to serve. Makes 4 1/2 doz.

title: hot ham and cheese
directions: Make a spread of butter, poppy seed, dry mustard and onion. Open buns.
Spread mixture on both sides.
Place 1 slice of ham on bun; put 1 slice of Swiss cheese on top of ham.
Replace top of bun and put additional spread on top of bun.
Wrap separately in foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 buns.

title: ultimate chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, combine cocoa and soda. Blend in 1/3 cup margarine.
Add water; stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in eggs, sugar and 1/3 cup margarine.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour in prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: basil garlic butter
directions: Mince in processor the basil leaves and garlic.
Add butter and pepper.
Chill until firm (about 1 hour).
Use with grilled fish or meat.
Also, use as spread on canapes or bread.
Can be frozen up to one month.

title: chinese rice casserole
directions: Cook beef with onion and pepper.
Mix all other ingredients in large casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: double crust chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into one pie crust.
Put on top crust; flute edges and cut slits in top.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: tracy's dog biscuits
directions: Mix flours, dry milk and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add eggs and brown sugar.
Add enough water to make a stiff dough.
Roll out; cut with bone shaped cutter.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: butterscotch bread
directions: Mix butterscotch and sugar.
Cut slightly thawed dough into small pieces (1/4-inch).
Arrange cut pieces of dough in a greased Bundt pan and put some butterscotch mixture in between the slices. Sprinkle excess mixture on top.
Let it rise overnight.

title: baked pork chops and vegetables
directions: Season pork chops to taste.
Place in a deep glass dish.
Add a layer of each:
squash, onion and potato.
Divide butter and place on top.
Pour 1 cup of water over the ingredients.
Cover; cook at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a greased 10-inch square glass dish.
Cut up butter in 4 or 5 pieces and drop onto sugar mixture. Pour in milk.
Do not stir.
Microwave on High power for 2 to 3 minutes, or until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from oven and stir thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and vanilla, so nuts are distributed evenly.
Spread fudge evenly in dish.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Cut into 24 pieces.

title: cheezy biscuits
directions: Cream butter in an electric mixer; add egg yolks and mix well. Gradually blend in cheese.
Blend in flour until thoroughly mixed.
Mixture will be a stiff dough.
Roll dough out on floured board and cut in circles.
Place on a greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
After biscuits are done and while hot, brush with melted margarine.
Sprinkle more cheese over the top.
(Can sprinkle a dash of garlic on each one.)

title: chiffon chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add hot milk a little at a time, stirring until smooth.
Add butter and return to double boiler; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour a small amount over egg yolks, add to mixture, and continue cooking until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch shell and top with meringue and brown.
Very good.

title: camper's cornbread
directions: Put 2 tablespoons margarine in two aluminum pie tins and place in preheated 450° oven to melt.
Put milk in mixing bowl. Add meal gradually until desired consistency is reached (not too thick, not too thin).
Add first 6 ingredients and mix well. Add melted margarine. Spray tins with Pam and fill with batter.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 12.

title: christmas morning bread
directions: Grease bundt pan.
Place frozen bread rolls, 18 small squares into pan evenly.
Shake 1 small dry pudding mix over bread.
Melt butter and mix with brown sugar.
Put mixture over bread.
Shake cinnamon and pecans over rolls.
Place towel over bundt pan and set it out overnight.
In the morning, preheat oven, bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool for 10 minutes; turn out onto serving dish and serve.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place chicken and broccoli in a greased dish.
Heat soups, milk, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and broccoli. Top with small package of Pepperidge Farm herb dressing.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and pour over dressing.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pickled squash
directions: Slice squash and onions.
Soak in salt for 2 hours; cover with water and drain well.
Boil sugar, vinegar and seed.
Pour over squash and let it stand 2 hours, then boil for 5 minutes.
Put in jar.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Spread each slice of bread with butter.
Place in buttered casserole size 13 x 9.
Sprinkle sausage, then cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and cheese.
Chill at least 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 8, generously.

title: rice pudding
directions: Wash rice.
Mix ingredients and pour into buttered pudding dish.
Bake three hours in very slow oven, stirring three times during first hour of baking to prevent rice from settling.

title: mama's old fashion dressing
directions: Spoon shortening into an 8-inch cast-iron skillet.
Place in a 425° oven for 4 minutes or until hot.
Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add 2 eggs and buttermilk, stirring well.
Spoon into hot skillet and bake at 425° for 35 minutes or until browned.
Cool; crumble cornbread into a large bowl.
Add bread cubes and remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: beer kraut
directions: Place kraut in Dutch oven.
Add beer to cover.
Add seasonings and V-8 juice.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Melt butter in small skillet.
Stir in flour and brown well.
Add 1 cup juice from kraut.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Stir back into kraut.
Add kolbasi.
Simmer covered 1 1/2 to 2 hours more.

title: mexican layered taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix together.
Layer ingredients in order given.
Serve with taco chips.

title: macaroni cheese casserole
directions: Boil water with 1 teaspoon salt and cook macaroni.
Do not overcook.
Scald milk and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Combine with macaroni.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake in unbuttered dish at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: butterscotch overnight cookies
directions: Mix sugars, butter and lard together.
Add eggs.
Sift soda, salt. cream of tartar and flour together and add to butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix and make into 4 rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° for 12 to minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Soak gelatin in lemon juice, then dissolve over hot water.
Blend cream cheese with mayonnaise and salt.
Stir in gelatin.
Whip the cream until stiff, adding sugar gradually during last of beating.
Fold in cream cheese mixture, fruit cocktail and nuts.
Pour into refrigerator tray lined with waxed paper.
Freeze until firm, for at least 4 hours.

title: cherry pudding
directions: In a 1 1/2 quart casserole pour pie filling.
Spread cake mix on top and dab slices of margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip topping.
Serves 4.

title: meatballs on a skewer
directions: You will need at least 6 metal 6 to 8-inch skewers.

title: picnic cornish hen
directions: Rub each hen with salt and pepper and 1 tablespoon mustard. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Place in square of foil and fold to center.
Add onion and tablespoon butter, then fold over the foil tightly.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes, then open foil and bake for 15 more minutes.

title: gourmet burger
directions: Add chili powder, onion powder and Worcestershire sauce to ground beef.
Shape into 4 patties (1/2-inch thick).
Wrap slice of bacon around each burger; broil or grill.

title: sparkle punch
directions: Combine soft drink powder and sugar.
Dissolve in milk.
Pour in 6 to 8 glasses.
Add scoops of ice cream.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump in undrained pineapple.
Swirl around to fill in corners.
Dump in cherry filling.
Swirl to even out.
Dump in cake mix to cover.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until brown.
Serve with whipped cream (Cool Whip) or ice cream.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute pepper, onions and celery in bacon drippings.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, mustard, sugar and seasonings. Simmer 25 minutes.
Add shrimp and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Sterilize jars. Wash, peel and mash figs.
Place figs, gelatin and sugar in large heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and boil 5 minutes, stirring often.
Pour in hot jars.
Wipe tops clean.
When cool, cover tops
with paraffin and let set.
Top with lids and rings.

title: ham glaze
directions: Blend together all ingredients, except white cloves.

Remove ham from oven 20 minutes before it is done. Slice fat on ham in crisscross pattern. Place cloves in ham and add glaze. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, basting if necessary. Instead of vinegar or cooking sherry, the liquid from maraschino cherries can be substituted.

title: friendship tea mix
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl, stirring well. Store mix in an airtight container.
To serve, place 1 1/2 tablespoons mix in a cup.
Add 1 cup boiling water and stir well.

title: microwave dish
directions: Mix, cover and microwave for 30 minutes.
Stir at half time.

title: stuffed hamburgers
directions: Fry bacon crisp; add egg and onion to ground beef.
Form into 4 equal balls.
Divide each ball in half and flatten.
Place 1 pickle slice, 1 cube cheese and crumbled bacon on flattened meat.
Flatten other half of meat; place on top of first half with ingredients sandwiched between.
Pinch and seal edges.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Spoon 1 tablespoon chili sauce on top of meat and bake for 10 minutes more.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine.
Add 1/3 cup of mix to 1 cup of hot water.
If you like yours a little more chocolatey, just add more cocoa.

title: russian potato pancakes
directions: In large bowl, toss potatoes with lemon juice.
Grate onion; squeeze out liquid and add to bowl with potatoes.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except oil.
Heat 1/2 inch oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Portion 1/4 cup measures of potato mixture into hot oil, spacing apart.
Cook until golden brown, about 3 minutes on each side, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep hot on baking sheet in 325° oven.
Repeat with remaining potato mixture, adding oil to skillet as needed.
Serve with applesauce if desired.
Makes 16 (3 to 4 inch) pancakes.

title: triple chocolate brownies
directions: Mix together cake mix and pudding and 1 to 2 cups water. Batter will be very thick.
Spread in cake pan.
Layer your chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° until done.
Very rich, but very good!

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder. Cut in Crisco. Add milk all at once; mix until soft. Roll to 1/4 inch thick. Cut into 6 squares. Place apple on each square & sprinkle cinnamon, brown sugar & dab of butter on each apple. Fold corners up over apple & pinch edges together. Place in baking dish, 1 inch apart. Pour liquid mixture over dumplings & bake at 375 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: easy hot fudge sauce
directions: Stir all ingredients, except vanilla, in a saucepan over medium heat; stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil; boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Serve warm over cake or ice cream.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: walnut cheese spread
directions: Mix cheese and butter thoroughly.
Stir in spices and sherry. Add walnuts.
Refrigerate, but let warm to room temperature to serve.
Yield:
3 cups.

title: boneless pork roast(4 to 6 pounds)
directions: Put apples and prunes in roast opening.
Tie it together.
Bake in 325° oven.
Combine sugar and salt.
Rub over prepared roast. Put on rack (fat side up) in shallow pan, 40 minutes per pound. Put small potatoes around roast.
(Spoon drippings over potatoes while they bake.)
One recipe pan gravy.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine onions and squash in large pan.
Sprinkle with salt. Set aside 1 hour to drain.
Combine sugar and vinegar; add celery and mustard seeds and bell peppers.
Bring to a hard boil while stirring.
Add drained squash and onions; bring to a light boil. Put in jars and seal.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme; mix until well blended.
Serve with fresh fruit and cookies as dippers. Makes 2 cups.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add other ingredients along with flour.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Pour into well-greased funnel pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Melt butter; add soups, onions, etc., and sour cream.
Put frozen potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Top with paprika and parsley.
You may also put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook.

title: badger stew
directions: Coat cubes of beef in flour.
Heat oil in large pan.
Add meat and brown.
Add other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add water as necessary.
Serves 8.

title: brenda's breakfast casserole
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in casserole dish.
Mix milk with eggs and seasonings.
Beat well.
Pour egg mixture over the ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes or until mixture is set and firm to touch.
You may layer ingredients in the casserole dish the night before and refrigerate.
You may also mix the egg mixture in separate container and refrigerate.

title: crepes marquis
directions: Combine eggs, flour, salt and milk; beat until smooth.
Let stand 30 minutes.
For each crepe, pour 1/4 cup of batter into hot, lightly greased skillet.
Cook on one side only.

title: dottie's homemade biscuits
directions: Combine flour with Crisco (I use a fork to mix).
Pour in buttermilk until dough is sticky, but not too moist to work with your hands.
Put handful of flour on surface.
Knead lightly 6 or 7 times.
Pat out dough to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out with floured cutter.
Place biscuits close together for soft sided biscuits or 1-inch apart for crusty sides.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes, until brown.

title: apple butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, rolled oats and apple butter.
Mix last ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts.

title: pineapple scallop
directions: Mix pineapple, flour, sugar, salt and eggs and pour into greased casserole.
Melt butter and add diced bread.
Put bread mixture on top of casserole.
Bake at 400° until brown on top (15 to 25 minutes).
(Good side dish with ham or pork.)

title: marzetti casserole
directions: Steam meat and rinse with hot water; drain well.
Microwave onion and green pepper in small amount of water for 4 minutes; drain excess water.
Combine with mushrooms and seasonings. Combine tomato soup, tomato sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce and add to meat.
Mix well.
Cook noodles in boiling water until almost tender; drain and rinse.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 2 cups meat sauce on bottom of pan.
Cover with about 1 1/2 cups noodles on top.
Spread 2 cups meat mixture on top.
Cover with half of cheese.
Repeat with noodles and then rest of meat.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
The last 10 minutes of baking, uncover and sprinkle with remaining cheese and heat until melted. Yields:
12 (1/2 cup) servings.
Calories: 140.
Fat:
5 grams.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in buttered casserole one half at a time. Alternate layers of cheese, crackers and broccoli.
Save some crackers and cheese for topping.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crawfish cornbread dressing
directions: Bake cornbread in 9x13-inch pan according to directions.
Also add 1/4 cup of sugar to mix.
Saute vegetables in butter, stir in seasonings, add broth and bring to a boil.
Add crawfish, continue cooking for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in crumbled cornbread to consistency you prefer.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Stir.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in order given and beat after each addition.
Add fresh apples and pecans.
Bake in tube pan at 250° about 2 hours or until done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and apples.
Mix well.

title: pork sausage soup
directions: Brown sausage, beef and onion.
Drain and add other ingredients except cabbage.
Mix well.
Stir in cabbage and cook until done.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place raw rice in bottom of casserole.
Brown pork chops in skillet, then arrange on top of rice or remove chops from skillet. Put rice in bottom, then replace chops.
Place slice of onion, tomato and pepper ring on top of each pork chop.
Pour can of beef bouillon over this.
Cover casserole and bake in oven at 315° for about an hour.
Add water if needed.

title: wet corn bread
directions: Add meal and water together and boil until thick.
Stir constantly.
Add the remaining ingredients together with the meal and water that has been cooked and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased baking pan (sheet cake pan).
Bake for 1 hour in a 375° oven.
Let stand to "set" for 15 minutes before cutting into small squares.

title: coconut icebox cake
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Cook over low heat until mixture coats spoon.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water and add to hot mixture.
Cool.
Beat egg whites. Add to cooled custard. Add 3/4 of the coconut. Add vanilla.
Pour mixture over angel food bits in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread whipped cream or Cool Whip over custard. Sprinkle with remaining coconut. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Freezes well.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch or two 8-inch pans.
Beat all ingredients except egg whites on low speed until blended (about 30 seconds).
Beat on high speed 2 minutes. Add egg whites and beat on high 2 minutes more.
Add fresh strawberries; mix well.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly in center.

title: chocolate pecan grahams
