directions: Combine melted margarine, brown sugar and pecans in saucepan. Cook until brown sugar is melted, stirring constantly.
Arrange graham crackers over bottom of jelly roll pan.
Pour brown sugar mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Let stand 5 minutes to melt chips; spread melted chocolate.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into small balls and bake at 375 degrees until brown.
Can be frozen before or after baking.

title: mexican beans
directions: Brown meat, chopped onions and chopped green peppers in skillet.
Mix all ingredients together and put in cooker.
Pour barbecue sauce over top and cook on low for 2 hours.
This is great for a family get-together.

title: mince cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well. Combine dry ingredients and gradually add to shortening mixture. Stir in mincemeat.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Frost if desired.
Makes 6 1/2 dozen.

title: western chili casserole
directions: Brown meat; add 3/4 cup onion and celery. Cook until tender; drain fat.
Add chili and pepper.
Heat.
Place layer of chips in ungreased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Alternate layers of chili mix, chips and cheese.
Reserve 1/2 cup chips and 1/4 cup cheese for trim.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese and onion.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into six pieces.
Coat with sugar and cinnamon which have been mixed.
Place in a greased Bundt pan. Mix remaining sugar mixture with margarine and pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no fat oatmeal apple raisin muffins
directions: Beat egg; stir in remaining ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Pour into 12 greased muffin cups until 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve cool or piping hot with butter.

title: low-fat pie crust
directions: Blend flour with Butter Buds.
Add oil gradually, mixing with a fork.
When all of oil is added, work mixture until it is the size of small peas.
Gradually add just enough water until dough is moist enough to form a ball.
Roll out and line pie pan.
If pie is cut in eighths, each serving of crust will have 4 grams fat.

title: tea recipe
directions: Bring 1 quart water to a boil. Remove from stove; add tea bags and steep 30 to 45 minutes. Take a gallon jug and fill with about a quart of water. Add sugar, lemonade and tea. Stir well and fill remainder of jug with water. Refrigerate. This may be made several days in advance to chill thoroughly. It keeps well for a week in the refrigerator without clouding.

title: mostaccioli casserole
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer half of the noodles, half of meat sauce and half of the Velveeta.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Quick and easy.
Can make ahead.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in 1/4 and dip in butter.
Roll in brown sugar. Sprinkle cinnamon over before baking. Bake at 250° until biscuits are done.

title: veggie burger
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
In a blender, finely chop the remaining ingredients.
Add the chopped vegetables to the ingredients in the bowl and mix thoroughly. Shape into patties.
Melt margarine in a frying
pan and cook over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.
Yield:
6 burgers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put in casserole.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs or any crumb topping.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ice cream delight
directions: Combine crackers and oleo.
Take out 1 cup of crumbs and set aside.
Line a 9 x 13-inch glass cake pan with remaining crumbs and press down.
In a large mixer bowl, combine softened ice cream, milk and instant pudding.
Beat at least 20 minutes.
Pour over crumbs.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
In a large saucepan, put the sugar, water, raisins, margarine, carrots and spices.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Cover the pan and let it stand for 12 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix corn, corn meal, milk, oil, soda and salt.
Spread half of mixture into greased 8 x 10-inch baking pan.
Add layer of cheese and layer of peppers.
Spread with half of mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese 5 minutes before done.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 10 servings.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Beat cake mix, pudding mix, oil, water and eggs for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add half of the German sweet chocolate to the batter; beat for half a minute.
Pour into tube pan.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: christmas bread
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar, egg and bananas.
Sift and add flour and soda.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and 1/2 the bottle of cherries, cut into small pieces.
Grease and flour loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Bread is done when inserted toothpick comes out clean. Makes 2 small loaves or 1 large loaf.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart baking dish, add bread.
In another dish, mix ingredient well.
Pour mixture over bread.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until brown. Serves 4 to 6.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and salt in saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. (Start timing when mixture starts to bubble around edges of pan.) Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute, until marshmallows melt and blend.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: cabbage  casserole
directions: Layer these ingredients in order as they are listed in a greased pan of your choice.
Be sure the tomatoes and juice plus the tomato can of water are last.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
This dish can be eaten with picante sauce.

title: orange balls
directions: Make into balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Decorate with tea leaves.

title: lazy wife cake
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make 3 holes in the mixture.
In one hole, put the oil.
In the second hole, put the vinegar.
In the third hole, put the vanilla.
Over whole mixture, pour the water.
Stir all together with a fork or spoon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and frost with any kind of frosting.

title: chilaquiles
directions: Saute onion and garlic in hot oil in Dutch oven until tender. Stir in tomatoes, chilies, cumin, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cut tortillas into fourths; fry in 1/4-inch hot oil about 5 seconds on each side or until softened.
Drain well on paper towels.
Layer half each of tortillas, tomato mixture and cheese in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with sour cream if desired.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips with margarine.
In a large mixing bowl, beat chocolate mixture with remaining ingredients, except nuts, until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes until center is set.
Cool.

title: white potato pie
directions: In
mixing bowl beat eggs slightly with mixer.	Stir in cream, potatoes,	sugar, vanilla, lemon and salt.
Beat until mixture is	smooth.
Place	in
unbaked
pastry shell on oven rack. Sprinkle
with
nutmeg.
To prevent overbrowning, cover edge of pie
crust	with
foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.	Remove foil
and
bake
to 20 minutes more or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: ray's pancake mix
directions: It's okay to double this recipe.
This recipe makes 9 to 10 normal sized pancakes or makes 3 to 4 fireman size pancakes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put salt over cukes, onions and peppers.
Let stand 1 hour. Mix rest of ingredients and pour over cukes.
Put in jar and refrigerate.

title: supper popover
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook and stir ground beef in skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, green pepper, 2 tablespoons flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Heat to boiling; boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Beat eggs, milk, oil, 1 cup flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt; pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with onion.
Bake until puffy and golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Sift together dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Divide dough in half. Chill 1 hour or overnight.
On lightly floured surface, roll to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut in shapes with cookie cutters.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° about 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Combine ground beef and flour in skillet.
Add onions and brown.
Pour off drippings.
Add tomato sauce, catsup, salt and pepper.
Pour into 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°. Top with cheese.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crescent links
directions: Place links in skillet with 3 tablespoons water.
Cover and steam for 5
minutes.
Open
and
separate crescent rolls. Sprinkle 1 to 2
tablespoons
cheese
on
roll.
Lay
link	on bottom edge and roll according to package directions.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes according to crescent roll directions.

title: end of garden relish
directions: Cook carrots and green beans.
Soak cucumbers, peppers, cabbage, onions and green tomatoes in salt water (1 cup salt and 1 gallon water) for 12 hours.
Drain well, then rinse in cold water and drain again.

title: nut bread
directions: Cream together the sugar and egg.
Set aside; thoroughly sift the flour, salt and baking powder.
Then add the dry ingredients to the egg mixture, alternating with milk.
Add the pecans.
Blend in vanilla.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan and let stand 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour pineapple over that.
Then box of dry cake mix.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Add layer of coconut, then layer of chopped nuts.

title: broccoli gourmet
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Combine soup, onions, eggs, cheese and mayonnaise.
Fold and mix good.
Layer broccoli and sauce in greased casserole dish.
Add buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: molded peach salad
directions: Combine orange jello and sugar; stir in 2 cups orange juice and lemon peel.
Heat until jello is well dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in buttermilk.
Chill until partially set; fold in fruit.
Pour into a 6 1/2 cup mold and chill until firm.
Combine sour cream and 1/4 cup orange juice. Cover and keep chilled.
At serving time unmold salad into a plate of lettuce.
Serve with sour cream dressing if desired.

title: fresh coconut pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients except coconut.
Add coconut and stir.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave peanut patties
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in 2-quart microwave dish. Cook 3 1/2 minutes on full power.
Take out and add peanuts and continue cooking on full power for 9 minutes longer.
Take out after 5 minutes and stir.
Cook the other 4 minutes.
Take out and add butter, vanilla and coloring.
Beat hard with a wooden spoon until creamy.
Pour into mini muffin tins that have been sprayed with Pam.
(If this hardens too fast, add 2 more tablespoons butter.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, vanilla and zucchini; beat.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown sausage and drain well. Put vegetables to cook with water to cover. Simmer until nearly tender. Add sausage, tomatoes and seasonings and simmer 20 to 30 minutes to blend flavors. You may omit sugar and put a packet of sweetener into individual bowls. Serves 10 to 12.

title: coconut cheese pie
directions: Melt butter and mix all ingredients.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: pierogi
directions: Mix in order listed.
Turn out on lightly floured board. Knead until elastic.
Roll out on board to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch circles.
Fill with 2 tablespoons filling.
Fold to semi-circle and seal edges tightly.
Boil gently in salted water for 5 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine chicken, onions and green pepper.
Layer alternately with tortillas which have been dipped into hot chicken stock just long enough to soften, in a 3-quart buttered casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese, chili powder and garlic salt.
On top, add the the following in order and layer: chicken soup, mushroom soup and tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: jessica's potatoes
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish (glass is okay).
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: durkee green bean casserole
directions: Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole all ingredients mixed together.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining 1/2 can of onions.
Bake, uncovered, until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: slap together cake
directions: Mix all together until moist. Do not overmix. Pour into 8-inch square buttered pan. Sprinkle over top the brown sugar and chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: pop's relish
directions: Grind veggies in food chopper.
Put the canning salt over all. Let stand overnight. Drain well.

title: vegetable quiche squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shred cheese; mix all ingredients and spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool before cutting.
Serve with salad for quick easy dinner.
Great for brunch or showers.
Serves many.

title: cream tacos
directions: Brown meat and season.
Add chilli and tomatoes.
Cook slowly 20 to 30 minutes.
Whip cream stiff and add to meat mixture with beans and cheese.
Heat slowly over low heat until puffy.
Shred lettuce and cube tomatoes.
Place in serving bowl.
Layer Doritos in bowl.

title: mogen david wine cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquid.
Beat to blend well.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes only or check with toothpick.
Grease Bundt pan with butter.
Sprinkle with white sugar.

title: lazy lady bar
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in large pan 10 x 15-inch.
Sprinkle evenly over oleo all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salsa casa
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve as a condiment with meats or as a dip for tortilla chips.

title: banana-nut-oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch muffin tin. In small bowl, mix 1/2 cup walnuts and 2 tablespoons oats.
Set aside.
In large bowl, mix remaining chopped nuts and oats with flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.

title: green pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate.

title: walnut pancakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into large bowl.
Stir in wheat germ, brown sugar, vanilla, oil, milk and egg.
Mix just until blended.
Let mixture stand for about 5 minutes while griddle heats.
Pour batter onto hot griddle.
Immediately sprinkle about 2 teaspoons of chopped walnuts onto each pancake. When bubbles form on surface, flip pancake.
Let cook about one more minute.
Serve with butter and hot maple syrup.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, bell pepper, carrot and salt.
Let this stand 1 hour, then drain.
Mix remaining ingredients; boil 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm; pour over cabbage.

title: orange whip drink
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in food blender until well mixed and foamy.
Serve immediately.

title: apple marmalade
directions: Wash, pare, core and slice thin the apples.
Quarter the orange and remove seeds (slice thin).
Add water and sugar; boil.
Add lemon and fruit.
Boil and stir until it thickens.
Yield:
6 or 7 (1/2 pint) jars.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Makes 1 cup of dip for veggies.
Great for veggies.

title: grandma murdock's butterscotch pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Cook in saucepan over medium heat until thick.
Add butter.
Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: pumpkin chip cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars. Beat in pumpkin, egg and vanilla. Combine the flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Gradually add to creamed mixture. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in a tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 275° or bake in an oblong pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: crispy parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix crushed crackers, cheese, salt, paprika, onion powder and pepper.
Blend milk and oil in another pan.
Dip chicken into liquid and then into crumb mixture.
Bake until tender, about 1 hour.
Mix leftover milk, half and half with water and use as fresh milk.

title: golden fruit punch
directions: Steep the tea bags in boiling water in a covered container for 5 minutes. Discard the tea bags. Combine the tea, pineapple juice, grapefruit juice, orange juice and lemon juice in a large pitcher. Add the sugar and stir until the sugar dissolves. Chill until serving time. Stir in the ginger ale and ice water. Serve immediately. Yield: 2 1/2 quarts.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute chopped garlic and onion in shortening; remove.
Salt, pepper and flour the meat; pound.
Slice into 1 to 2-inch strips and brown.
Return onion and garlic to pan.
Add undrained mushrooms, ketchup and consomme.
Simmer for at least 1 hour, or until meat is tender.
Add sour cream.
If desired, thicken with flour and water.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4 generously.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook salad macaroni; rinse with cold water.
Combine all other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add to macaroni.
Chill at least 6 hours before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 cup tomato soup, beef, onion soup mix and bread crumbs and mix thoroughly. In baking pan, shape firmly into 8 x 4-inch loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until meat loaf is no longer pink.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake for 30 minutes.

title: mass sherry cake
directions: Beat 10 minutes. Put in greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake 50 minutes at 350°. Turn out hot; prick with meat fork. Pour glaze (2 cups xx sugar and 1/2 cup sherry) over cake.

title: spiced sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Measure all dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Blend in margarine, egg and milk.
Mix until smooth, then make round balls.
Put them on ungreased pan, then use fork to press down on balls.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Cook at 350° until firm or 1 hour.

title: reese's cup candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips, paraffin and candy bar in double boiler. Mix the first 3 ingredients and roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip into melted chocolate mixture.
You can freeze these to last.

title: super soup pot
directions: Combine all ingredients in large cooking pot.
Bring to a boil, lower heat, cover and simmer 45 to 55 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli and onions.
Combine the other ingredients and pour over the broccoli and onions.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: indonesian sauce
directions: Puree all ingredients in food processor and marinate chicken for 4 to 6 hours, then barbecue.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef tips over rice
directions: Dip beef in flour.
Brown in Crisco oil; add salt.
Add water; simmer.
Add more water as needed.
Add onion.
Cook until tender. Make gravy.
Cook a little longer.
You can add mushrooms.
Cook rice; drain well.
Pour beef and gravy over rice.
Serve with a tossed salad.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in bottom of flat dish. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Beat Cool Whip, confectioners sugar and cream cheese and put over crust.
Beat lemon pudding and milk and put on top.
Cover with Cool Whip.
May also use chocolate or any other pudding.

title: pizza spaghetti pie
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper and milk. Press firmly onto bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: milk madness
directions: Pour milk into shaker; add gelatin.
Shake for 1 minute.

title: strawberry pudding freeze
directions: Pour milk into bowl and add pudding mix.
Beat slowly with hand beater or at lowest speed of electric mixer until blended, about 2 minutes.
Blend in whipped topping and strawberries.
Pour into shallow pan and freeze about 4 hours or overnight.
Serve in ice cream cones or dessert dishes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine celery, chicken, mushroom soup, salt, onion and lemon juice.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top, then crushed potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: irish sweet bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, oil, vanilla and buttermilk.
Spoon into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fri-chik pot pie
directions: In a large oblong baking dish, combine soup, milk and thyme. Stir in vegetables and Fri-Chik.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until mixture begins to bubble.

title: jerky
directions: Soak meat overnight in water, 1/4 cup salt and brown sugar. In the morning, rinse lightly.
Lay on trays in Little Chief Smoker.
Add salt and pepper and garlic salt lightly.
Cook 8 to 10 hours or until done.
Use hickory chips or your choice of smoking flavors.
Don't use aluminum pans or bowls.

title: rice crispy date balls
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and dates in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until almost smooth (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, cereal and nuts.
Let cool.
Shape into balls and dust with powdered sugar.

title: artichoke and bacon squares
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine with bacon, green onions and sour cream.
Set aside.

title: banana bread
directions: To sour whole milk, add 1 tablespoon vinegar to 1 cup milk.

title: brother george's pie crust
directions: Put egg and vinegar in a cup.
Add milk to make 3/4 cup. Combine and add rest of ingredients.
Makes enough for 3 or 4 pies.

title: hot spiced tea(similar to wassail)
directions: Mix and keep in sealed container.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: plum coffee cake
directions: Cream 1/4 cup
butter

Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add egg, pumpkin and remaining ingredients.
Grease cookie sheet.
Drop mixture by spoonfuls onto the cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: grandma dot's 14 day pickles
directions: Wash and cut crosswise 2 gallon pickles.
Put in a crock.
Pour over them 1 pint salt and 1 gallon boiling water.
Let stand 1 week.
On 8th day, take out pickles and rinse them and crock.
Pour 1 gallon water (boiling) and let stand 24 hours.
On ninth day, drain and wash.
Put back in crock, adding a lump of alum the size of walnut in boiling water.
On tenth day, make syrup.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until brown and remove from pan.
Fry meat until brown, break bacon into meat, add 3 to 5 drops hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce and mix.
Add 1 cup water and simmer 15 minutes.
Open clams and save juice; grind clams.
Put clams, juice and meat mixture in large soup pot.

title: cheese deviled eggs
directions: Mash yolks. Mix with remaining ingredients and stuff whites.

title: baked spinach casserole
directions: Combine cheeses and margarine.
Add spinach and eggs that have been beaten with flour.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into 1 1/2-quart glass baking dish.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mom's peach creme pie
directions: Place peach halves down in unbaked pie shell.
Pour over mixture of sugar, flour, butter and eggs.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and place in 450° oven for 10 minutes, then 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Combine and cook first 6 ingredients at medium heat until hard ball stage.
Add last 2 ingredients.
Stir until pink.
Pour into greased round cake pan.
Makes one round cake pan size patty.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Mix crushed chips with garlic salt.
Dip chicken in melted margarine.
Roll in potato chips.
Place on baking sheet and pour remaining margarine and chips over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sand tarts
directions: Beat butter in a large bowl at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add 3/4 cup powdered sugar, beating well.
Add flour to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.

title: salsa cream cheese
directions: Mix cream cheese with fork until smooth.
Start adding salsa by forkfuls (slightly drained).
Keep adding salsa until you have reached a nice dipping consistency, not runny (approximately 4 to 5 forkfuls).
Serve with nachos.
I especially like to this with pretzels.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Spread into a 10 x 15-inch pan, greased and lined with waxed paper.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on confectioners sugar covered towel.
Roll up like a jelly roll in towel and wax paper. Let cool 15 to 20 minutes.
Unroll.
Continue to cool.

title: snowball cake
directions: You will need 1 large angel food cake.

title: marinated chicken for the grill
directions: Wash and cut up chicken.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add chicken and marinate for several hours.
Drain marinade.
Grill chicken, basting with marinade.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients.
If too dry, add more buttermilk; if too runny, add more flour.
Preheat grill to 400°.
Cook pancakes until golden brown on both sides.

title: hanky panks
directions: Unroll dough into 2 long rectangles.
Press into the bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pinch edges to form a crust.
Press out perforation in dough.
Lightly spread dough with mustard.
Evenly sprinkle dough with ham, onion, green pepper and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown and bubbly. Cut into squares and serve hot.
Can be made ahead; refrigerate until ready to bake.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 quarts boiling water.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Do not chill in refrigerator!
Pour into large punch bowl.
Add other ingredients. Stir.
Garnish with pineapple and cherries.

title: april fools ice cream cones
directions: Note:
Need 20 to 24 flat bottom ice cream cones.

title: potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes and cool.
Slice in half lengthwise.
Hull out potatoes with spoon, leaving 1/2-inch potato on skin.
Drop potato skin in deep fat and fry until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Top with grated cheese and bacon bits and broil in oven until cheese melts.
Remove from oven and top with sour cream.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts, set aside.
Cut shortening into flour until crumbly.
Add milk and stir with fork until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Roll dough out into large rectangle, like jelly roll.
Sprinkle apples with cinnamon, then sprinkle apples over dough.
Roll up and slice (1/2 inch).
Place in melted butter pan.
Pour sugar water over slowly.
Bake about an hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well; add eggs and beat.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Add mashed bananas; mix well; add chopped nuts.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes one large loaf.
(For 2 small loaves, cut baking time to 45 minutes.)

title: cucumber salad
directions: Cut up vegetables into bite sizes.
Mix vinegar, sugar, salt and oil together.
Pour over vegetables and let set for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake for 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: italian lemon sponge cookies(makes 30 cookies)
directions: Blend eggs and sugar together.
Add melted margarine.
Stir in, by hand, the flour and baking powder.
Add milk and lemon extract.
Form into small balls and bake at 500° for 6 minutes on top rack in oven.
Dip into icing while warm.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cool Whip.
Add Cool Whip last. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.
Keeps up to a week.

title: sausage fondue
directions: Place bread in bottom of greased 8 x 12-inch dish.
Top with cheese, then sausage (drained).
Beat eggs with milk and mustard. Pour over top of casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Completely coat 13x9 pan with oil,
put remaining ingredients in pan, stir until blended.
Bake at 350° For 35-45 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese potato soup
directions: Mix all together and let simmer.

title: calico beans #1
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Set aside.
Brown bacon, then crumble into beef.
Drain 1/2 liquid of kidney and lima beans. Drain all butter bean liquid.
Combine all beans in large bowl. Mix brown sugar, ketchup and vinegar.
Add mixture to beans. Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Stir when half done.
Great for potluck dinners!

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Melt margarine and mix.
Pat in oblong cake pan. Bake until light brown. Let cool.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let cool.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Whip the chilled Carnation milk into cream.
Add jello, lemon juice and whipped cream into the creamed mixture above.
Pour into cooled graham cracker crumb crust (crust recipe on crumb box is great).
Add a sprinkle or two of the crumbs on top of cake before baking.
May also sprinkle with chopped nuts if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar, then add pineapple.
Add all other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator to get cold.
Mold in mound. Roll or sprinkle with pecans.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine chicken stock, garlic powder and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Remove cover during last 15 minutes to brown.

title: classic alfredo
directions: Cook fettucine according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, melt butter or margarine over medium heat.
Stir in heavy cream and milk.
Gradually stir in cream cheese, then Parmesan cheese until well blended.
Stir in parsley.
In small pan, cook scallops and add to sauce.
Pour over hot fettucine.
Serves 6.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 10 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Combine navy beans, chicken broth and water in large kettle. Cook for 1 hour.
Add carrots, potato, cabbage, canned tomatoes and cook for 30 minutes.
Set aside.

title: corn flakes macaroons
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Stir in cream of tartar and almond flavoring.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff and glossy.
Fold in almonds, coconut and corn flakes cereal.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto well-greased baking sheets.
Bake in oven at 325° about 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove immediately from baking sheets.
Cool on wire racks.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove skin and all visible fat from chicken parts.
Place in baking dish.
Wash hands, cutting board and utensils with hot, soapy water.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix egg, sugar, flour and juice. Cook until thick. Add margarine and cool.
Dice the apples.
Add with remaining ingredients.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add vanilla, then flour and baking powder, one cup at a time.
Beat well.
Spread 3/4 of batter over greased cookie sheet/jelly roll pan with sides (do not flour pan), then cover with filling.
Dot rest of batter by spoonfuls here and there over filling (it will look like a map).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.

title: french toast
directions: Mix thoroughly the eggs, milk, sugar and salt in a pie pan or baking dish.
Melt butter in skillet until bubbly, but not brown. Dip bread in egg mixture, turning to coat both sides.
Place in skillet; fry until golden brown.
Turn and brown other side. Yield 2 servings.
